title: party oyster crackers
directions: Mix ingredients together and toss with crackers until oil is absorbed.

title: pork chops and sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add pork chops.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes slowly on each side or until brown.
Remove chops from pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add 1/2 cup of pineapple juice, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon to drippings and mix well. Add sweet potatoes; turn to coat with liquid.
Return pork chops to pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir in pineapple and green pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Transfer chops to warm platter.

title: walter's chili
directions: Mince onion and garlic; cook in oil until brown, then add turkey and brown.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except beans, with turkey; cook over low heat for 3 hours.
Add kidney beans 5 minutes before serving.

title: easy sherbet punch
directions: Mix orange juice and soft drink.
Pour over sherbet in punch bowl, or mix in pitcher.

title: wiener bean pot
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir together beans, onions, ketchup, water, brown sugar and mustard.
Add wieners, pushing pieces below surface of beans to prevent overcooking.
Cover.
Microwave at High 11 to 13 minutes.
Stir before and serve.

title: dried beef and chicken casserole
directions: Place 1 small jar of dried beef in bottom of casserole dish. Wrap pieces of chicken breast with a piece of raw bacon and place in dish.
Cover with 1 can of undiluted cream of mushroom soup. Optional:
Cover with drained mushrooms.
Bake covered at 300° for 2 hours.
Turn temperature up to 350° for another 20 to 25 minutes still covered.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs and blend well.
Pour in oil and mix on medium speed until there is no trace of oil, up to 3 minutes.
Add flour and spices.
Blend well.
Add pumpkin and mix on low speed until well blended.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: fried mountain trout
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and black pepper in Ziploc bag.
Shake well.
Put as many fish as you can in bag and shake to coat with cornmeal mixture.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients by hand.
Lay rolls in pan.
Put mix on top of rolls.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Get out all juice.
Mix milk, pineapple, lemon juice, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts. Arrange cherries on top for decoration.
Chill overnight.

title: wassail(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Combine cranberry juice, sugar and water; stir to dissolve sugar and heat to boiling.
Tie spices into cheesecloth bag; add to the liquid.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Just before serving, add fruit juices.
Serve steaming hot.
(May be served from 30-cup electric coffee server.)

title: crme de menthe bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease one 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat the white sugar with 1 cup of the butter or margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in the eggs.
Then stir in the flour, salt, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Mix until combined.
Pour batter into the prepared pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cook, then frost with Crme De Menthe Frosting.
Refrigerate until set.
Then spread melted chocolate topping over top.
Let sit until set.
Cut into bars.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add vanilla, then fold in flour as gently as possible.
Bake in angel food pan at 325°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until top is nicely browned.

title: sweet spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together. Then drain. Then separately heat all other ingredients on stove. Then add ground beef and onion mixture. Simmer.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: 1. Clean the chicken cutlets.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Wash, drain and break spinach and lettuce into a salad bowl. Add vinegar, water, sugar and salt to bacon fat in skillet.
Bring to a boil and pour over spinach and lettuce.
Toss and add crumbled bacon.

title: quick chinese-style fried rice
directions: Bring water to a boil in a small saucepan, stir in instant rice.
Remove from heat, cover, and let stand for 5 minutes.
In a skillet, melt butter and lightly cook egg.	Add onion and rice and saut, stirring over medium heat until mixture is slightly browned.
Mix water with soy sauce and stir into rice.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: virginia creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add milk; stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add salt, pepper, onion, hot sauce, parsley and chicken.
Cook until chicken is thoroughly heated.
Stir in soy sauce.
Spoon over toast slices.
Serves 6.

title: 5 bean dish
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef.
Add onions; drain fat.
Stir in refried beans, tomato sauce, green chilies and taco seasoning.
Layer 1/2 tortillas on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 meat mixture; sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat sour cream, soup, cheese, and 3/4 stick of margarine in saucepan until melted; add onions. Place frozen hash browns in a 9 x 13 pan. Pour melted mixture over hash browns. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with corn flakes. Drizzle 3/4 stick margarine over. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This recipe can be prepared ahead just leave cornflakes off until ready to cook.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soups, sauce and chiles.
Melt in Velveeta.
Keep warm in chafing dish or crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Move to baking dish or leave in skillet if it can be placed in oven.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over chops.
Combine soup and water and pour over rice and chops.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or longer.

title: quick peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, peanut butter, water and egg; stir by hand until dough forms. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 9-11 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately top each cookie with candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge; remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pineapple pecan cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer.
Add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: mrs. richards' honey dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add vinegar, lemon juice and grated onion.
Pour oil in mixture, beating constantly.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut lettuce into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients, except Catalina dressing and Doritos.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over salad and stir in Doritos.
Serve immediately.

title: gazpacho
directions: In electric blender combine 1 tomato, 1/2 cucumber, 1/2 onion, 1/4 green pepper, pimiento and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Blend, covered, on high for 30 seconds, until vegetables puree.
In a large bowl combine pureed vegetables with remaining tomato juice, 1/4 cup olive oil, vinegar, hot pepper seasoning, salt and pepper. Refrigerate, covered, for 2 hours.
Refrigerate 6 serving bowls.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash dry beans and let soak overnight in about 6 cups of water.
Next day, drain, if any water is left, and put in slow cooker. Cover with 5 cups of water and pour in box of Zatarain's red bean mix.
Also add sausage, if desired.
Cook about 6 hours on medium heat. Serve on rice.

title: how to cook a christmas turkey
directions: Cook however long it cooks.

title: tex-mex tostada soup
directions: Brown meat with onion in large pan.
Drain well.
Drain tomatoes; chop.
Reserve juice.
Add tomatoes and juice to pan with beans, tomato sauce, water, picante sauce and cumin.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Top with cheese, chips and lettuce.
Add additional picante sauce as desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and allspice.
Mix liquid mixture to dry mixture.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Chop tender portions of broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Crumble bacon; mix with broccoli, onion and cheese.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: bananas barefoot
directions: Put Grand Marnier, butter and sugar in large skillet.
Stir at high heat until it starts to caramelize.
Cut bananas lengthwise, then peel and saute until golden.
Put on top of ice cream.
Spoon sauce over ice cream.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: no bake cheese pie
directions: Beat together until creamy the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Fold in whipped cream until evenly distributed.
Fill pie shell and top with pie filling.
Chill several hours.
If desired, individual graham crackers may be used.
Just chill in bowl and fill as needed.

title: broccoli-orange salad
directions: Break broccoli flowerets into bite-size pieces (about 1 1/2-inches).
Thinly slice onion and separate into rings.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix sugar, melted oleo and bourbon.
Add nuts and vanilla. Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Place in freezer until firm. Roll into balls and put into refrigerator.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush Oreos. Mix next 4 ingredients. Mix pudding and milk. Put cookies in 9 x 13 pan. Mix pudding and Oreos together. Put in pan. Sprinkle with crushed Oreos.

title: diet copper pennies
directions: Drain carrots.
Combine green peppers, onions and carrots. Bring all other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over carrots. Refrigerate.
Will keep 6 weeks.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all in blender and blend for 2 minutes.
Pour in a 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: phyllo spinach rolls
directions: Grate cheese.
Add eggs, parsley, and spinach (if using). Blend well.
Unroll phyllo.
Slice dough into 3rds lengthwise (4x12 apprx)
Re-wrap 2/3 of dough in plastic.
Freeze.
On wax paper, take one sheet of phyllo and brush liberally with butter. Top with 2 more sheets, brushing each layer with butter. Place 1 Tbsp of cheese mixture 1-inch from edge of sheet.
With fingers, roll dough over mixture twice.
Fold in edges of the dough and continue rolling tightly.
Place seam side down on cookie sheet. Brush tops with butter and bake at 400°F for 15 minutes and until golden crispy.

title: roast
directions: Wipe roast with damp paper toweling.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder, if used.
Place meat on rack in roasting pan deep enough to hold the drippings.
Insert a meat thermometer (registers 130° for very rare, 140° for medium and 170° for well done).

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add the flour, milk and sugar; whisk continuously until the mixture has the consistency of pudding.
Add the beaten egg yolks and bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat and add the lemon juice.
When cool, mix with the fruit.
May also use any fresh fruit.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: spaghetti salad for six
directions: Mix all together and let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: french bread
directions: Melt all ingredients and spread on both halves of bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Thoroughly cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well. Make a paste of cocoa and red food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix salt, vanilla and buttermilk together.
Add cake flour alternately with buttermilk mixture to creamed mixture.
Mix baking soda and vinegar together, then fold into batter.
Do not beat or stir. Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix. Spread bean mixture evenly. Layer remaining ingredients in the following order:
avocado dip, sour cream, olives, tomatoes, onion, chilies and cheese.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Combine all ingredients, except seafood.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add seafood.
Cook slowly until done.
May eat over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream shortening and vanilla; add sugars and cream until light. Add eggs and pumpkin. Beat well. Add all dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture. Beat until smooth. Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes or until done; cool. Cut into bars. Makes 32 bars.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
In an electric mixer, beat the egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
When whites become firm, gradually add sugar, then vanilla and almond extract.
When the mixture forms stiff peaks and looks shiny stop beating and add nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on to the cookie sheet.
Place in the oven and turn off the heat.
Leave overnight.
Don't peek!!!!!!!!!!!

title: wisconsin torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, oleo and nuts together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven. Do not brown.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread crushed onion rings evenly over top.
Bake, uncovered , at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Heat margarine or butter until melted. Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper. Cook until bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in broth and milk. Heat until boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir for approximately 1 minute. Stir in chicken and vegetables. Pour mixture into prepared pie shell. Cover mixture in pie shell. Turn edges under just like a pie. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: magic pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg and water; sprinkle over flour mixture.
Add vinegar and lightly stir until forms a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until ready to use.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Wash cranberries.
Add sugar and water.
Cover and cook until skins burst (8 to 9 minutes). Add oranges, salt and spices. Cook 1 minute.
Cool and serve with meat or poultry.

title: ham soup
directions: Place ham in enough water to cover it.
Bring to boil; skim top.
Lower heat to simmer.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery and onion; simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove 2 cups broth and cool. Add sour cream to cooled broth and pour back into soup.
Add rice. Cover for about 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: char's quick lemon pie
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together and pour in pie crust.
Chill. Serve with a dollop of Cool Whip and a candy lemon slice.

title: hardy sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble bread in pan.
Fry sausage, drain and crumble over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt together.
Pour over sausage and bread.
Top with grated cheese. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until soft.
Add bread crumbs.
Add beef, seasonings and egg.
Form balls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter; dredge in flour and saute in remaining butter until lightly browned.
Add 1 cup stock or water with 1 1/2 tablespoons of flour blended in it to the meatballs.
Cover and simmer until thickened (10 minutes).

title: crock-pot stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off of peppers.
Remove stems and set tops aside to use later.
Clean out peppers.
Brown ground beef and remove grease.
Add onion, celery, rice, milk, egg, salt, pepper and chili powder to ground meat and mix well.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
In pot, combine tomato soup and water.
Place pepper tops in bottom of pot and set stuffed peppers on top of them to prevent peppers from spilling.
Cover and simmer on high for 2 hours.
Spoon sauce over peppers when serving.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wash roast.
Place in roast pan.
Add wine, salt, pepper, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Brush liquid mixture over roast.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight. Remove from refrigerator.
Peel and slice potatoes and carrots. Wash and slice mushrooms.
Add to roast pan.
Dice onion and add to roast.
Cover and bake in a 325°
oven from 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Use 15 in
x 11in baking dish (or two 10 x 12 dishes). Crumble cornbread into 5 quart mixing bowl.
Add salt, pepper and celery salt.
Add sage by rubbing together between palms of hands to separate.
Mix well.
Parboil celery and onion in a small amount of water until crisp tender.
(Celery and onion combined yield about 4 cups after par-boiling.)
Cool slightly;
thoroughly mix into cornbread mixture.
Divide mixture (6 to 7 cups each) evenly between two 5 quart mixing bowls.
Break eggs into 2 different small bowls (3 eggs in each bowl); slightly beat eggs and add to each mixing bowl.
Divide broth between bowls, mixing well.
Mixture may be loose.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugars together; stir in eggs, then vanilla. Combine flour, salt and baking soda together; mix in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 10 minutes.
For chewy cookies, remove when gloss has just left. Bake until golden for crispy cookies.
Be sure to guard this dough well as it has a tendency to disappear before you can get it in the oven.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine 1 stick melted butter with chopped candy bars.
Melt on low in the microwave.
Cream sugar and the remaining 1/2 c. softened butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Slowly add in skim milk alternately with flour and mix well after each addition.
Stir in candy bar and butter mixture and pour into a well greased bundt pan.

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add milk, egg and shortening. Bake in 8-inch square greased pan in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Finely chop carrot and onion.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon of oil, cook carrot and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
In a large bowl, mix carrot, ground meat, uncooked orzo, bread crumbs, salt, rosemary, egg and 1/4 cup of water.
Shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
In same skillet over medium-high heat in 2 tablespoons of oil, cook meatballs half at a time until browned.
Remove to a bowl as they brown.
Stir flour into 2 3/4 cups of water until smooth.
Stir flour mixture and the vegetable bouillon into drippings in skillet; heat to boiling, stirring to loosen brown bits from bottom of skillet.
Boil 1 minute.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and cut apples.
Melt butter in bowl.
Add sugar, flour, walnuts and egg.
Mix ingredients.
Put cut apples in 9-inch round greased glass pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour batter over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper; add to soups.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Take skin and bone out of chicken when chicken has boiled until tender.
Layer spaghetti, chicken and soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: old-fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Put shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl and beat on high for 2 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Beat until blended.
Add sifted flour mix.
Beat well, about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: squash casserole 2
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Spray 9 x 13 baking dish with Pam.
Drain squash and mix it and above ingredients, except for 1/2 cup of Ritz crackers.
Mix well in baking dish and add remaining Ritz crackers over the top of the casserole.
Bake in oven until bubbling.

title: anita's chicken enchiladas
directions: Fill flour tortillas with chicken pieces. Make soup mixture with next 5 ingredients and add to tortillas.
Roll each filled tortilla and place in 9 x 12-inch pan side by side.
Pour remaining soup mixture over top of all.
Garnish with olives and more shredded cheese.
Bake uncovered at 300° until hot through and through and cheese is melted.

title: sunshine slush
directions: Boil water; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Boil gently, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Meanwhile, in blender, combine bananas and 1/2 of the pineapple juice; blend until smooth.
Stir into cooled syrup.
Stir in the remaining pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade and lemon juice.
Stir in vodka or rum.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch plastic container and freeze.

title: breaded chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then cover with crumbs, pressing them into chicken. Brown in about 1-inch of Crisco in a skillet on both sides. Remove from skillet and put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion salt.
Pour oil from skillet into baking pan; cover bottom of pan with about 1-inch of water.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until when inserted with a fork, chicken breaks apart.
Check occasionally while baking and if pan is dry, add a little water.
The secret to my chicken is using Kellogg's crumbs, Crisco oil and don't overbake.

title: pecan avocado salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Refrigerate until thickened to consistency of unbeaten egg white, then whip until foamy.
Beat in sour cream and mayonnaise until thoroughly blended.
Fold in pecans, avocados, onion, celery, green pepper and salt.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold and garnish as desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: busy day cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together in bowl. Add shortening and milk, unbeaten egg and flavoring all at once. Beat all ingredients together well with a rotary beater for 2 minutes.
Pour in a greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Bring oleo, water, shortening and cocoa to boil in pan.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add baking soda to buttermilk and add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Ice while still warm.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fiesta ranch potatoes
directions: Shake mix and potatoes in Ziploc bag.
When potatoes are well coated, bake at 425° in single layer on pan sprayed with Pam. Bake approximately 40 minutes until brown.
Serve with Ranch dressing or chili dip.

title: cereal with a difference
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in syrup, marmalade and salt.
Drizzle over popcorn in a large bowl; toss gently.
Add coconut, almonds and dates.
Toss gently until thoroughly blended. Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Stir halfway through baking time; remove from oven.
Stir in raisins and cool in airtight container.
Makes 2 3/4 quarts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix until thick pudding and milk.
Do not overstir because it will be too thin.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in dairy topping.
Add vanilla.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, add layer of vanilla wafers, layer of bananas (sliced) and layer of pudding mixture.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Heat over low heat until smooth.
Serve with chips, crackers or raw vegetables.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix butter, cheese and flour with hands.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls and press down in pan with wet fork.
Bake at 325° until tan in color.

title: down south yam cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, cream sugar, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Cut up yams; add to creamed mixture, beating until well mixed.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg; mix well.
By hand, fold in pecans, raisins and drained pineapple.
Spoon batter into prepared pan; spread evenly. Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan for 10 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onions in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (no salt); place in casserole dish.
Stir soup and cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg.
Stir until blended.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with browned bread crumbs.
(Can be made ahead.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over low heat until thick (stir constantly).
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients, folding in whipped cream last.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy pan, stirring constantly until smooth and thick; cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk, then add melted butter and syrup.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cover top with pecans.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually; add vanilla. Sift flour, salt and soda together. Add the eggs, one at a time, to the batter mixture. Add flour and milk alternately using some flour last. Pour half of mixture into 2 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 300° until done.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Just like they make in school.

title: garlic chicken salad
directions: Cook green beans about 6 minutes until tender but crisp. Drain well and chill.
If chicken has skin on it, remove and then cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Set aside and chill.
Shell and devein shrimp; chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large frying pan on medium until cheese is
melted.
Pour	into
quart casserole.
Top with seasoning mix
and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Coat a soup pot with nonstick cooking spray. Add the mushrooms and saute over high heat for 5 minutes or until soft, stirring frequently. Add the chicken broth, onion powder and pepper; bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine, then blend with brown sugar.
Beat in eggs. Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix in vanilla.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together ingredients to form soft dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet; press cookies with a fork and then bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Combine the brown sugar, flour and salt. Cut in (with pastry blender or 2 knives) the cold margarine.
(Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for the topping.)
Add the baking soda, milk and egg; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with reserved topping, Heath bar pieces and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Mix gelatin and water until dissolved.
Add fruit and blend and then add nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Reserve remaining mixture at room temperature.
After bottom is set, spread with yogurt.
Top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: ten minute microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 4 to 6-cup glass container, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and dash of salt.
Microwave 4 minutes on High power.
Stir well and microwave 3 minutes.
Add margarine and blend well.
Now microwave 2 minutes or until peanuts are golden brown.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
Use margarine to grease cookie sheet. Do not use nonstick spray products.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: easy strudel
directions: Mix flour and margarine together; set aside.
Then mix egg yolks, vinegar and water together.
Add this to flour and margarine.
Add a little more flour as needed.
Cut dough into three pieces and chill overnight or at least two hours.
Roll dough fairly thin on lightly floured board.
Sprinkle with crushed graham crackers; next with grated apples, then sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and a little flour, chopped nuts and bits of butter. Roll like a jelly roll.
Bake at 375° on ungreased baking sheet about 30 minutes.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In large shallow
baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: country fried steak
directions: Crush crackers with rolling pin. Mix egg and milk. Dip steaks in eggs. Sprinkle with Johnny's seasoning. Cover both sides with crushed crackers. Brown steaks in hot oil then simmer on low for 40 minutes (covered).

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Mix oregano, salt, paprika and garlic together.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then add the bouillon cubes and mushrooms.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Add cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Arrange bread in a greased 9 X 13 inch casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Scatter sausage pieces over cheese.

title: gravy and sausage
directions: Heat butter in saucepan.
Add flour; cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not allow mixture to brown.
Slowly add hot milk to butter-flour mixture, stirring constantly with a whisk until sauce is thickened and smooth; simmer for 5 minutes.
Strain and keep warm.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix by hand and spoon into a well-greased muffin pan; bake as other biscuits.

title: winter punch
directions: Mix tea with sugar and fruit juices.
Chill well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale, orange slices and cherries.
Makes 10 quarts.
Serves 75.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Pour into a tube cake pan. Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add coconut and pecans.
Lightly brown; set aside. Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 of the mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 jar caramel topping on each pie, then sprinkle coconut mixture over.
Repeat layers.
Freeze.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite-size pieces.
Blanch (cook briefly); drain and add salt.
Mix them with the diluted soup, crushed crackers and cheese and turn into a greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until the vegetables are tender.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat cream to boiling. Reduce heat to medium. Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Add butter, a little at a time, stirring as you add. Add salt and pepper.
Makes 1 1/4 cups sauce, enough for 1/2 pound of pasta.
Sprinkle the other 1/4 cup Parmesan over pasta.

title: seasoned sizzlers
directions: Marinate sausages in mixture of remaining ingredients on low in crock-pot.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients with the mayonnaise.
Use on salads.

title: mississippi jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add spices to flour.
Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately with flour mix.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake at 325°.

title: liz's tex-mex dip
directions: Spread on a large plate or platter.

title: cherry-black walnut ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients in freezer can; fill can to line with milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spinach dip
directions: Dip vegetables or crackers into this.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix & bake at 350° in 3, 8-inch pans (greased & floured) for 25 to 30 min.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over rye bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with mustard.

title: dump cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix by hand until blended. Pour in ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Frost with butter icing or dust with powdered sugar.

title: hill country potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt in covered saucepan until fork tender, about 35 minutes. Peel and dice or partially mash potatoes. In small skillet, fry bacon until crisp. Add diced onion and saute until tender but not brown. In bowl, mix cornstarch or flour, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper. Stir in vinegar and water until smooth. Add to bacon; simmer, stirring until thickened. Pour hot dressing over potatoes and add 1/4 cup minced onion, parsley, celery seeds and radishes. Serve lightly tossed and garnished with celery leaves.

title: pina colada squares
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Gradually add cream of coconut to cream cheese.
Mix well until blended with electric mixer.
Stir in run, fold in whipped topping, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Spread over crust and sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: banana nut pudding
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
With wire whisk, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in bananas and walnuts. Pour into dessert dishes.
Pudding will be soft-set and ready to eat in 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Mix water and sugar; boil until forms a hard ball when rolled between fingers (or dropped in cool water).
Pour over beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla flavor; beat well.
Add nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pie crust by mixer
directions: In small mixing bowl, mix together flour, salt; add shortening.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until pieces are the size of small peas (15 seconds).
Add water; beat on low just until moistened (10 to 15 seconds).
Form dough into 2 balls. Makes 2 (9-inch) single crusts or 1 (9-inch) double crust.
Roll out to fit pie pan.

title: corn muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add cornmeal and mix well.
Beat egg.
Add milk and shortening to dry ingredients; mix.
Bake in muffin pans 25 to 30 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients and add a handful of salt.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, drain through colander.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Boil 1/2 hour, then seal in jars.

title: date delight
directions: Crush cookies and mix with butter.
Put in bottom of 8 x 8-inch dish. Chop dates and cook in water with salt until soft. While hot, add marshmallows and nuts.
Spread this over cookie crust and chill.
Whip cream with vanilla.
Spread over date mixture.
Sprinkle crushed crumbs over top for garnish.
Chill overnight.
Freezes and keeps well.

title: chile chili
directions: Brown ground beef, pepper and onion together in a large pot. Add all other ingredients. Simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar with oleo.
Add salt and vanilla.
Combine soda, baking powder and flour; set aside.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternately with dry ingredients and sour cream.
Refrigerate dough for at least 6 hours, preferably overnight, covered.
Grease cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough on heavily floured surface; sprinkle flour all over the top so you can work with dough.
(It will be very sticky, so be generous with flour.) Roll out to desired thickness (about 1/4-inch); use cookie cutters.
Bake for 8 minutes, or until bottoms of cookies are barely brown.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Mix 4 cups of flour with baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar and caraway seed.
Stir in currants or raisins, making sure they are separated.
Add buttermilk all at once; mix with fork to form a dough.
Sprinkle approximately 1/4 cup of remaining flour on your work surface.
Turn out the dough; knead for 5 minutes, until dough is smooth.
Use only enough of remaining flour to prevent dough from sticking.
Form dough into smooth, round loaf; press into the pan.
Cut a cross 1/2-inch deep, across the top of the dough with a sharp knife or razor blade.
Bake for 1 hour, until loaf is lightly browned and sounds hollow.
Remove bread to a wire rack.
Rub top with butter; dust with sugar.
Cool 8 hours before serving.

title: noodles and ground beef
directions: In a large saucepan, saute meat, onions and green pepper.
Add peas, corn, green beans, oregano, bay leaf, salt, pepper, tomatoes, Pure, Worcestershire, soy sauce and enough water to cover.
Simmer, uncovered, about 45 minutes.

title: best-ever bread and butters
directions: Gently stir salt into thinly sliced cucumbers; cover with ice cubes.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours or until cucumbers are crisp and cold.
Add more ice if it melts.
Drain; add onions.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring quickly to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
Add cucumber and onion slices and bring to boiling point.
Pack at once in hot jars.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water, 212°, for 30 minutes.
Remove jars from canners and complete seals.
Makes 8 pints.

title: mexican corn bread salad
directions: Bake cornbread; cool.
Then cut or crumble into bowl.
Chop tomato, onion and bell pepper into bowl with bread.
Add jalapeno and cheese and crumble bacon.
Mix well with plenty of mayonnaise (about 1 pint) and chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes; peel while hot.
Cream butter; add eggs and beat well.
Add sugar and mix well.
Put in potatoes, evaporated milk, milk, cinnamon and coconut; mix well.
Pour into pie crust. Top with second crust.
Make small slits or poke holes with fork in top crust; sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fudge mint cake
directions: Prepare
cake
mix
according to directions and add 1/2 cup creme de menthe to the batter.
Bake as directed.
Cool 15 minutes.
Cake
will
still
be warm, but not hot.	Spread the jar of	chocolate
fudge ice cream topping on top of the cake. Put in refrigerator.
When
cool, mix one carton of Cool Whip and 1 tablespoon	creme de menthe together and frost the cake with this. Return to the refrigerator.

title: pinocha squares
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Mix in chocolate bits and nuts.
Spread in an 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° no longer than 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: rotini vegetable medley
directions: Cook rotini; rinse and drain.
In a large bowl, put rotini, mixed vegetables, bacon bits, Italian dressing, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onion in small amount of fat in a heavy skillet.
Cook very slowly until the meat turns white. Drain off accumulated fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: my favorite snack:  a basket of fruit
directions: Put ice cream in the bowl. Cut up fruits.
Put in the fruits. Eat it!

title: amandine
directions: Mix mandarin sections with sugar and almonds, chill thoroughly.
Serve as side dish for ham, pork or curry, or as a topping for waffles, pancakes or ice cream.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter.
Use the paper to grease pan prepared for the treats when finished.
Melt marshmallows.
Once melted, pour box of Rice Krispies in and stir until blended well.
Put in pan that's greased, then spread out treats.
Wait 30 minutes, then cut into desired figures.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into prepared cracker crust. Refrigerate 12 hours.
Servings:

title: baked flounder
directions: Thaw fish fillets enough to separate.
Arrange in baking dish; sprinkle with lemon juice and seasoned salt.
Combine soup and milk in bowl; mix well.
Spread over fish.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and cheese; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Mix flour with spices, roll chicken in seasoned flour and brown chicken in hot oil.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Cover with 2 cans beer, lower heat and simmer for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Thicken liquid with 1 to 2 tablespoons cornstarch in 1/2 cup water.
(Add more water, if needed, during cooking chicken.)
Serve over rice or with mashed potatoes.

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix vinegar and soda in a small cup and let stand.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Make a paste of the cocoa and a little food color.
Add to creamed mixture, then add rest of coloring.
Add buttermilk, salt and cake flour alternately, then add the vanilla.
Stir the soda and vinegar, then add.
Mix well and pour into two oiled 8-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and split each layer in half. Spread icing between layers and on top and sides.

title: aloha dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Blend in next five ingredients.
Chill 1 hour or until serving time.
Serve with crackers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan with cooking spray and put a layer of pecans in the bottom of the pan (optional) and set aside.
Put 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a gallon size plastic bag and set aside.
Melt the butter and 2/3 cup sugar over low heat.
Open 2 cans of biscuits and cut into quarters. Place cut biscuits in the tube pan and pour half of butter and sugar mixture over coated biscuits.
Repeat with the other 2 cans of biscuits and remaining butter/sugar mixture over coated biscuits.
Pour any remaining cinnamon sugar on top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
When done, immediately invert on a serving plate.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: sauce(poultry and beef)
directions: Combine ingredients, except parsley.
Blend thoroughly, then add parsley.
Yields
approximately 1/2 cup.
Spread over meat.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Rinse peas and carrots under cold water and drain.
Melt margarine in a 2-quart saucepan and stir in the flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in meat and vegetables. Remove from heat.

title: white chocolate orange dream cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Instant tea may be used with or without sugar.

title: spicy lemon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add Bubble-Up and pineapple juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: ham delights
directions: Cut package of rolls in half (whole package at once).
Put bottom half back into pan.
Mix margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion together.
Spread bottom half of rolls with half of the mixture.
Put ham and cheese over this. Spread mixture on underside of top half and put this over bottom half.
Put in preheated oven (350° to 400°) for 10 minutes. Cut rolls apart and serve.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Note:
You may substitute pecans instead of peanuts.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake at 350° until chicken is tender.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: english tea biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In a saucepan, bring raisins, fruits and water to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently until all water is absorbed.
Set aside and cool.
Sift dry ingredients together, minus the sugar.
Cream shortening with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Bring to boil the pineapple, sugar and lemon juice. Add gelatin and let cool. Then add cheese and whipped cream. Mix together and let jell.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, egg, parsley, mustard, mayonnaise and pepper and stir to blend.
Add crab meat and toss lightly with fork.
Shape cakes with a light touch and chill for about 1 hour. Cook 3 minutes each side in 2 tablespoons of oil and 2 tablespoons of unsalted butter (can use all butter).
Yields 8 to 9 cakes.

title: lemon icing
directions: For each cup of heavy cream, mix 1 teaspoon unflavored gelatin and 2 tablespoons cool water.
Heat over low heat until melted. Cool to room temperature. Whip the cream until it begins to mound. Slowly add gelatin in steady stream while still beating.
When the cream stiffens, it is ready.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to directions on box.
Add broccoli for last 4 minutes, drain.
In a skillet heat butter over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned.
Stir often. Add soup, milk, parmesan, pepper and fettuccine to chicken.
Cook through, stirring often.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Combine apples, eggs and salad oil.
Sift together rest of ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Spread mixture in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except butter, almonds and noodles.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter; add almonds and noodles and sprinkle on top.
Bake 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nuts, in a double boiler. Stir as it melts 5 to 8 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients with a beater.
Pour mixture over a large amount of chicken pieces.
Let set about 3 or 4 hours and drain. Put on grill.
Cook until brown.

title: creamed corn muffins
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal and all dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
In large measuring cup, mix buttermilk, egg and corn.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Put into prepared muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: souffle asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup in saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice and gelatin which has been softened in cold water.
Beat in softened cream cheese and
sour
cream.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in drained cut asparagus and chopped celery.
Pour into an oiled 1 quart loaf
mold or mold of your choice.
Chill until firm. Unmold
and garnish with hard-cooked egg slices or garnish of your choice.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; blend to desired consistency.
Freezes well.
Makes 5 cups of salsa.
Keeps well in refrigerator for a week.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Remove necks from squash and slice thin or chop.
Combine with onion, butter and salt.
Put in pan with small amount of water. Cut body of squash in two and scoop out seeds.
If seeds are not too large, combine with contents of pan, or may be discarded. Place squash cut side down on top of other ingredients in pan. Cover and boil until tender, but still firm.
Remove squash and arrange in pan coated with Pam.
Mix chopped ingredients with cracker crumbs, cheese, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir and mash with fork.
Heap into cavities of squash and bake at 350° until lightly browned on top, about 20 minutes.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Mash cheese with a fork.
Beat egg yolks and add to cottage cheese.
Stir in other ingredients and beat by hand until smooth. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake for 15 minutes at 475°, then 15 minutes at 375° (1/2 hour in all).

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: In a bowl, mix ground meat, parsley flakes, salt, pepper, onion, soy sauce, eggs, garlic powder and ketchup. Form into meatballs and brown.
Remove from pan to drain.

title: pork chops in cream
directions: Marinate chops in 1 cup Calvados or apple brandy the night before.
This makes the meat tender and tasty.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, heat butter and oil.
Add pork chops; brown on both sides.
Add salt and pepper, then the mushrooms and onions. Cook, turning occasionally, until pork is tender, about 15 minutes. When done, remove chops, onions and mushrooms; keep warm.
Add Calvados to skillet and scrape bits clinging to the bottom.
Skim away any grease from the liquid.
Gradually add cream and cook until slightly thickened.
Pour over pork chops and vegetables. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: children's play finger paint
directions: Mix flour and water with liquid detergent.
Add desired color food coloring.
Finger paint to create a masterpiece.

title: philly ham spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, deviled ham, pimiento, onion and pepper.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Form into a ball and cover with sliced almonds.
Serve with Triscuits or your favorite snack cracker.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together egg, shortening and sugar.
Add milk, flour and berries.
Mix well, then fill muffin pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° or until brown.

title: swiss schnitzel
directions: Place cutlets on waxed paper.
Flatten to 1/8-inch thick, using a mallet or rolling pin.
Beat well the eggs, salt and pepper.
Dredge cutlets in flour, dip in eggs and coat with breadcrumbs.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken, onion, carrot, celery, salt and bay leaf in 8 cups water until chicken is done, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove chicken from broth. When cool, remove the skin and bones and dice chicken.
Strain the stock and discard vegetables.
If necessary, add enough water to make 1 quart.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Spray lightly the bottom of casserole dish with Pam.
Pour dry cake mix in dish.
Add canned peaches with juice; cut butter into pats and place on top of peaches and cake mix.
Wiggle some butter down into mixture.
Cook for about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the macaroni until tender, drain.
Cook frozen vegetables until tender.
Mix together and season with the Italian dressing to suit your taste.

title: date loaf
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder over dates and nuts. In a bowl, beat egg yolks. Add sugar, flour and fruit mixture. Mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken, skin side down.
Mix soup and seasoning package from box of rice and 1 1/4 cups water.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: "the italian" spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown garlic in oil with sausage; then add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add basil and serve over spaghetti.

title: honey of a corn bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.

title: johnnycake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg, oil and milk.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until ice cubes are crushed.
Serve immediately.

title: lois' white frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Beat constantly over boiling water until stiff peaks form.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
This is good on coconut cake or devil's food cake.

title: fish casserole
directions: Boil
haddock and drain.
Break up and put in greased 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Pour
the mushroom soup over fish.
Sprinkle minced onion,
then
sprinkle a layer of crushed crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the chicken, celery, rice and water chestnuts and put into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Spread mayonnaise over top of mixture, then slice the eggs over the top.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Put half into bean pot.
Wash salt pork and place in center.
Add remainder of beans, salt, pepper, mustard, molasses and 4 cups cold water.
Cover.
Put into slow oven and bake 8 hours.
Add more water, if needed.

title: katie's spinach onion dip
directions: Blend ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Serve in a hollowed out bread loaf with fresh vegetables and bread chunks for dipping.
This is a quick and easy dip that is very tasty!

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Carefully mix with well-beaten egg yolks and rum.
Beat egg whites until they are stiff and gently fold them into the chocolate mixture.
Pour into individual molds and chill for at least 4 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in 2 1/2 or 3 quart casserole. Bake 25-30 minutes at 350°. Though there's mayonnaise in the recipe, it freezes very well. To freeze, do not cook prior to freezing.

title: date pudding
directions: Place soda in boiling water and let cool, then add melted butter.
Add egg, beaten well.
Add dates, flour, baking powder and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and onion.
Add egg.
Gradually beat in milk.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 16 small ones.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cheese butter dips (biscuits)
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Mix grated cheese with flour and then stir in milk until dough is the consistency of biscuit dough.
Roll out dough on floured board or cloth, then cut into biscuits.
Place biscuits in melted margarine, turning once to coat well.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Boil first 9 ingredients together slowly for about 1 hour. Then add shredded cabbage and continue cooking for 1/2 hour or so.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine water, sugar, honey, vinegar, catsup and lemon juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and thicken with paste made from cornstarch and water.
Great over meatballs or chicken.

title: special barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling, lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage, salt and pepper in oblong dish.
Spread evenly. Pour soup over cabbage.
Lay pepper over cabbage.
Cover with cheese.
Spread dressing over top of cabbage.
Pour oleo over dressing evenly.
Bake at 350` for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: 1) Heat chicken broth in a medium to large sauce pan.
As it is heating, add the hash browns.
Bring to a soft boil, reduce heat and add *gravy mixture.
Cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
Serve. Top with shredded cheese if desired.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey and onion.
Drain.
Add vegetable alphabet soup and 1 can water.
Simmer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt
oleo
in a casserole dish.
Beat eggs; add flour, salt and
sugar.
Blend	until
smooth.	Add corn;
mix well. Pour mixture
into oleo; but do not mix.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Slash franks every inch.
In a skillet, brown franks in oil. Add onions with chili powder.
Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in soup and water; simmer a few minutes stirring often.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice the cooked potatoes into baking dish.
Pour syrup made by boiling brown sugar, butter, water and salt over the potatoes. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: school house peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, crunchy peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, salt, eggs, soda, baking powder and vanilla together in large bowl in mixer.
Add flour and mix well by hand.

title: yellow party cake
directions: In a mixer bowl cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy, scraping bowl frequently.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat at medium speed (about 2 minutes) until light and fluffy.
Scrape bowl frequently.
Stir together flour, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk, beating at low speed after each addition.
Beat 1 minute at end.
Turn batter into 2 greased and lightly floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool thoroughly on wire racks.

title: sausage balls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine uncooked sausage with cheese.
Mix or knead until well blended (you can also use a food processor to mix the dough and it works real good)!
Add biscuit mix and blend thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes until nicely browned.
Serve hot.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook 1st four ingredients 20 minutes with lid on.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Cook until tender with lid on.
Add soup and cheese. Watch carefully so cheese won't burn.
Sometimes you may need to add water to thin it out.
Also good after it's been frozen.

title: shrimp dish
directions: Combine butter and salad dressing in a 3-quart pot.
Cook shrimp in ingredients until done.
Serve in bowls and dip toasted bread in mixture.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix dry and liquid ingredients together to form a ball like a pie crust.
Cut in half.
Roll 1/2 on foil (bottom) and put in jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Roll other 1/2 on wax paper (top crust). Cover bottom with 1 can cherry pie filling, cover with top crust and remove wax paper.
Seal edges.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes (until a light brown).
Cool then frost with 1 cup confectionary sugar with 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 Tbsp. milk. Sprinkle with crushed nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: barbecue beef cups(exported from mastercook; serving size: 5.)
directions: Brown hamburger; add sauce, onion and brown sugar. Simmer. In greased muffin tin, put 1 biscuit in each cup and shape into a cup. Spoon hamburger mixture into cups. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sunday dinner roast
directions: Add meat and desired spices (I use all of them) and vegetables, bay leaves and broth into slow cooker.
Cook on low for 8 to 9 hours.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix crumbs, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter; reserve.
Blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs on low speed until moistened, about 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of the batter (about 2 1/2 cups) into pan; sprinkle with half of the reserved crumb mixture.
Spread remaining batter evenly over crumb mix; sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle cake with Vanilla Glaze.

title: coconut peanut butter bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place 50 (1 1/2-inch) paper baking cups on cookie sheet.
In a medium size mixing bowl, combine the peanut butter, sugar and egg; stir until well blended.
Press 1 1/2 teaspoons of mixture into each baking cup.
In small bowl, combine milk and coconut; mix.
Put 1 teaspoon of the peanut mixture. Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: old fashion coconut pie
directions: In large bowl mix all ingredients and stir well.
Place on medium fire until thickened, remove and pour in pie shell (of your choice).
Place in refrigerator or room temperature until ready to serve.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: Cook together in saucepan, rice, broth and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Turn heat way down and simmer 14 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Add chicken, peas, onion and curry powder.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
May top with grated cheese.

title: light turkey soup
directions: Strip carcass of any large pieces of meat; dice enough meat to make 2 cups.
Set aside.

title: streusel topped banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease bottoms of muffin pans (15).
Mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and cinnamon.
Reserve.
Beat bananas, oil, milk, vanilla and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients, all at once, just until flour is moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Divide batter into 15 cups.
Sprinkle reserved mixture over top of batter on muffins.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from pan.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips approximately 2 minutes in microwave (longer if necessary).
Stir in milk, marshmallows, margarine and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: boursin (dip)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with mixed crackers and Pepperidge Farm pumpernickel or sesame sticks.

title: luscious lime salad
directions: Fold together all ingredients.
Chill 3 hours and serve.

title: icebox sandwiches
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to package.
Refrigerate until set.
Fold in whipped topping or Cool Whip and chocolate chips. Place 24 graham crackers on baking sheet.
Top each with 3 tablespoons of filling.
Place another graham on top of them. Freeze for 1 hour or until firm.
Wrap individual in plastic wrap and freeze.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ikrah (ee-krah)(russian origin)
directions: This is a spicy mixture that can be used as either a sauce or a dip.
Bake eggplant 1 hour at 350°, then slit skin on one side to drain while cooking.
Peel cooked eggplant, skin the tomatoes, then chop very fine the eggplant, tomatoes and onions.
Mix them all together along with other ingredients.
May be served warm as a sauce or chilled as a Fritos dip.

title: dietetic applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
In large bowl with mixer on high speed, beat margarine and Twin sugar substitute until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg until blended.
Gradually add flour mixture; beat until combined. Add applesauce; beat until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Pour batter in pan.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes, until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Let cool completely.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Combine with eggplant, rice and cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender and drain. Alternate the noodles, corned beef, cheese, soups, milk and onion in greased casserole (2-quart container).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves about 10.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix one package of cream cheese and other ingredients.
Roll into a ball and harden in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover ball with other package of cream cheese.
Excellent on party bread or crackers.
Ball should be completely white.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix together chicken or celery soup, oleo, milk and prepared mustard.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain sauerkraut and noodles. Layer in pan.
Pour top mixture over top, then layer chopped onions, corned beef and cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top. Cover.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles up and cheese is melted.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onion in a 4-quart saucepan.
Cover about 4-inches with water and cook until tender. Add water to about 5-inches from top.
After tender, add milk and butter. Bring to a scalding boil, then add egg and flour mixture which is called "rivels".
Sprinkle over milk and potato mixture and stir constantly. Add a little at a time.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine and add to all other ingredients.
Mix well. Drop
by 1/2 teaspoon on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Drop far apart. Bake at 350° for 5-6 minutes or until brown.
Allow to cool completely on foil.
Remove by peeling foil from cookies.

title: chicken in wine in no time
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces to coat.
Brown chicken well on all sides in oil in skillet. Sprinkle with onion soup mix; pour in white wine.
Add a little water.
Cover.
Simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: grammaw's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and lard (melted) together.
Add beaten eggs. Then add flour, soda and baking powder.
Add last four ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tex-mex tortilla appetizers
directions: Combine cream cheese, green chilies, green onions, black olives and garlic salt in a small bowl.
Spread 1 heaping tablespoonful of cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up jellyroll fashion.
Place seam side down on baking sheet; cover and chill 2 hours.
Slice each tortilla roll into 4 pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth. Pour into 2 round floured cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Caramel Frosting.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend together.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake for 40 minutes in 325° oven.

title: potato soup
directions: Place water and vegetables in pot and cook until tender.
Pour off water and save.
Saute 2 tablespoons onion and parsley in margarine.
Add flour and cook 1 minute.
Add stock and skim milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese and baking soda.
Mix well and add vegetables and water they were cooked in.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Add apples.
Drop large spoonfulls into hot oil.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Remove and coat in sugar.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cool whip. Chill at least 2 hours. Fold in cool whip when serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain kidney and lima beans. Add pork and beans and other ingredients as listed.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Refrigerate.
When ready to use, place in a 350°
oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Bake, uncovered, if you prefer less juice.
Stir well before serving.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir by hand.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake in preheated 325° oven approximately 30 minutes until glossy and set.
Serve warm with sliced bananas and whipped cream.

title: aunt bess' potatoes
directions: Cook onion in oleo until translucent.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Add cooked onions to mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: melting moment cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients in a bowl. In a larger bowl, mix margarine until smooth. Beat in flour and vanilla until well blended. Refrigerate 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart. Flatten with fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes
or until edges are brown. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: old-fashioned cabbage
directions: Fry
out the fatback until brown.
Remove from skillet. In the skillet
or
Dutch
oven,	add the cabbage and turn to medium heat.
Stir
to
coat cabbage with grease.	Cover with lid	and cook
slowly until desired tenderness.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: candied carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, cranberry sauce and sugar in skillet; simmer on low heat until cranberry sauce melts, stirring often.
Drain carrots.
Add carrots to cranberry mixture, stirring well.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable canapes
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in next 4 ingredients. Cut 2 (1 3/4-inch) rounds from each bread slice.
Spread with 1 teaspoon cream cheese mix, top with vegetables as desired.
Makes 32 canapes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello with the hot water; cool.
Follow directions on cake mix, using 3 eggs and jello instead of the water.
After baking the cake (timed according to the package), frost cake while still hot.

title: mexican casserole(in the microwave)
directions: Place taco chips along the bottom of a microwave-safe baking dish.
In a separate microwave-safe bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients (except the cheese!) and microwave on HIGH for 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave another minute.
Pour over chips and top with cheese.
Cover and microwave on HIGH for 3 minutes.

title: turkey-vegetable saute(low-fat)
directions: Coat a wok or large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add turkey; saute 5 minutes. Add mustard and next 5 ingredients; saute 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients; cook an additional minute, stirring constantly.
Serve warm.
Yield:
2 servings (serving size:
1 1/4 cups).
Calories 175.
Fat grams 2.3.

title: corn pancakes
directions: Cut corn from cob and scrape cob for additional corn milk. Sift dry ingredients together.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Split franks lengthwise.
Place in a large saucepan.
Mix flour with 3 tablespoons water in small saucepan, blending until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over franks.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a full boil in a large pan.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add cereal; mix well. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: basic layer cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Beat sugar and Crisco until creamy, adding eggs one at a time.	Sift flours together; adding to sugar Crisco mixture alternating with milk.
Add flavors.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan (no flour).
Scatter pecans on bottom, then the coconut over the pecans.
Mix cake as directed; pour over nuts and coconut.
Blend sugar, butter, vanilla and softened cream cheese.
Drop by teaspoons over unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° until done (about 40 minutes).

title: best-ever turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in cooking bag and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Brush turkey with oil, sprinkle with seasonings and place in a large size Reynolds oven cooking bag (14 x 20-inch) with nylon tie.
Put carrots, onions and celery inside bag around turkey.
Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 (1/2-inch) slits on top of bag.
Bake for 1 3/4 to 2 3/4 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: pico de diane
directions: Mix well and chill.
Best with Tostitos.
(May also add jalapeos and black olives.)

title: egg casserole
directions: Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut carrots in half crosswise, then quarter each piece lengthwise.
Toss with oil.
Put crumbs in paper bag.
Shake carrots in bag to coat.
Place in single layer in greased baking dish.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: soda pop cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients except the confectioners sugar; mix well and pour into the baking dish. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool completely. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, slice and serve. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and eggs; mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Spread marshmallow cream on warm cake; cover with Chocolate Frosting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Line bottom of pan with the apples.
Top with the remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: taco crescents
directions: Brown beef and drain off grease.
Stir in seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Stir in cheese.
Place rounded tablespoonful of mixture on each roll and roll up.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemonade
directions: In a large pitcher, dissolve the sugar in the hot water and let cool.
Stir in the lemon juice and the cold water.
Add 6 to 8 ice cubes and chill.
Serve in tall glasses with sprigs of mint.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add Crisco; mix. Add a little water at a time until dough is medium (still sticky, but not wet).
Let rise for 10 minutes. Dip dough in flour before rolling. Roll out very thin on floured surface about 6 to 8-inches in diameter. Cook on hot, flat surface until light brown.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out size of saucer.
Fill 1/2 with fruit mixture.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Fold over and crimp edges.
Crust freezes well.

title: taco salad(mexican)
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sour cream and taco seasoning and set aside. On a platter, put a layer of bean dip.
Next layer, put sour cream mixture.
Layer of onions, layer black olives, tomatoes, cheese and lettuce.
On top, put a tomato wedged open with cheese in the middle.

title: pink potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes in a small amount of water until tender; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Chill before serving.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: nine day pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 24 hours in salt water (one box salt).
Soak 24 hours in powdered alum water (1 teaspoon per gallon of water). Soak 24 hours in clear water.
Soak for 5 days in vinegar and allspice (1 tablespoon per gallon of vinegar).
Take pickles out on fifth day, slice, and pack in plastic or enamel pan a layer of pickles and a layer of sugar.
Let stand until pickles have absorbed all the sugar.
Pack in jars and fill with liquid out of pickles.

title: brownies
directions: With hand mixer, cream together the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until very smooth.
Add dry ingredients while continuing to mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 10 1/2 x 15-inch pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar. Stir and let set until slightly foamy. Combine flour, soda and Crisco. Add yeast mixture and combine to form soft dough. Make into biscuits and let rise in warm place 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake about 10 minutes in 400° oven. Dough can be stored in tightly covered container for up to 2 weeks.

title: maple walnut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots into 1/4-inch thick slices. Cut onion into thin rings. Cut green pepper into thin strips. Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water (salted) until just tender (8 to 10 minutes). Drain. Combine with onion and green pepper in a large bowl. Stir together remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables. Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Drain to serve for salad. Leftover vegetables may be returned to marinade. Yields 5 cups.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place unbrowned meat and vegetables in casserole.
Pour tomato soup and water over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 275° for 6 hours.
Serves 6.

title: maple biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine brown sugar, sour cream, egg, and maple flavor in a medium bowl; set aside.
In a large bowl stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, allspice, and salt.
Using a pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture; stir in sour cream mixture until moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Quickly knead dough by gently folding and pressing dough for 10 to 12 strokes or until nearly smooth.
Pat dough to 1-inch thickness.
Using a floured 2-inch biscuit cutter, cut out the dough.
Place 1 inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until bottoms are brown and sides are firm.
Remove from baking sheet.

title: orange coconut cookies(for diabetics)
directions: Combine sugar substitute with orange juice and vanilla.
Cream butter.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine with butter and liquid.
Knead in the coconut.
Shape dough into roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Cut into slices 1/8-inch thick and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 10 minutes or until brown around edges.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Mash bananas; set aside.
Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Add buttermilk, flour mixture and bananas.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake pulls away from side of pan.

title: pineapple-banana pie
directions: Cook pudding mixed with sugar substitute, pineapple juice and milk until thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Mix well.

title: spiced cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin, salt, cinnamon and cloves in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in orange and apple.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corinne's cherry salad
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 11-inch glass Pyrex dish.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: mini cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla.
Put vanilla wafer in cupcake liners, 1 to a cup.
Pour in mixture; filling about 3/4 full. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300° until done (begin to crack and tops are puffy).
Remove from oven.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes.
(An indentation will form as they cool.) Top with cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Cover bottom 10-quart pot with olive oil.
Add Italian seasoning and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and then let simmer 2 hours.
To make pizza sauce, add 1 tablespoon oregano. Yields enough for three meals to serve 4 people.
Makes enough to put in freezer.

title: health salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together cabbage, carrots, pepper and onion. Mix together vinegar, sugar, oil, celery seed and garlic salt. Pour over cabbage mixture. Cover; marinate in refrigerator overnight. Makes about 7 cups.
