title: squash casserole
directions: Slice onion and squash; steam together for 5 to 8 minutes. Mix rest of ingredients, except stuffing.
Spread half of stuffing on bottom of a casserole dish.
Add squash mixture on top.
Spread remaining stuffing on top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown together the meat, onions and celery; drain well. Mix both
soups,
water, chili powder and 1/2 of the noodles, along with meat mixture.
Pour in casserole dish (greased) and top
with noodles.
Bake
for
minutes
May add cheese on top just before serving.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Season the meat, then brown slowly in a heavy skillet. Add water to about 1-inch; cover and cook slowly about 1 hour. Spread the sauerkraut over the pork. Sprinkle the brown sugar. Add the onion and apple. Cover and cook slowly 1 more hour. Serves 6.

title: ho' made chilly
directions: Cook the beans for 2 hours or until done.
Place hamburger in large kettle.
Chop up the onions, peppers and garlic.
Mix in with hamburger.
Put in the black pepper and chili powder.
Let it cook while the beans are cooking.
When the beans are cooked, put in the hamburger mixture, then put in the tomato juice and ketchup.
Let it all blend in for about an hour.

title: fudge nut layer bars
directions: In a saucepan, combine chocolate pieces, cream cheese and evaporated milk.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into deep dish unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until almost firm.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add milk with flour.
Bake at 350°; test for doneness with toothpick.
Ice with chocolate frosting.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine pie filling, milk and egg in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and 1/4 cup of the coconut.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill about 4 hours. Spread whipped topping over pie and sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: microwave taco dip
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Mix taco seasoning according to package.

title: jello mold - cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, orange and sugar; let marinate for awhile. Add cranberry mix to remaining ingredients and set in refrigerator.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine and cocoa together.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and spoon batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with miniature marshmallows.
Spoon frosting over marshmallows.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in hot milk.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Mix well and add to squash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cover top with buttered bread crumbs and put under broiler a few minutes until slightly browned.

title: zuppa di ceci(chickpea soup)
directions: Heat olive oil in medium-size saucepan.
Add onion, cook over low flame until tender, about 4 or 5 minutes.
Add tomato and cook for 3 minutes.
Add chickpeas (undrained), garlic, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over high flame.
Cover, leaving lid somewhat off pan and simmer for about 25 minutes.
Fry bacon or microwave it until bacon is crisp.
Drain and add to soup mixture. Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Add molasses.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake
at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: sunday special coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan or a 9-inch round cake pan.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt and set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat egg until frothy, then beat in the 3/4 cup sugar and melted butter until well combined.
Add milk and vanilla and stir until blended.
With a wooden spoon, beat in flour mixture until well combined.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle topping evenly over batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool partially, in pan, on a wire rack.
Cut into squares while still warm.
(This can be reheated.)

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners (24).
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill the liners with the cream cheese mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Top each with a spoonful of filling and a spoonful of nuts.
Serves 24.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pat into round cake pan.
Prick all over with a fork.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cut in triangles while warm. Remove from pan when cool.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Cut cantaloupe in half; remove seeds.
Cut up pulp and put into a double boiler with sugar.
Mix cornstarch with a little cold water and add to cantaloupe.
After mixture thickens, add beaten egg yolks and salt; cook a little longer.
Cool.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Spread with meringue made from egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar; flavor with lemon.
Brown meringue in oven at 325°. Cool before serving.

title: reduced fat meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Make meatballs the size of large walnuts.
Saute in margarine or bake in 325° oven until cooked through.
Serve with rice, noodles or pasta.
Makes 6 servings.

title: summer squash-microwave
directions: Place squash salt, pepper, and butter in microwave safe dish. Microwave on high 5 minutes.
When finished Place cheese on top and allow to melt.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into ball with hands.
Coat with pecans and chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease (can use Pam) two loaf pans. Mix ingredients well and pour into loaf pans.
Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: easy thanksgiving dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter or margarine.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Toss in croutons, apples and pecans. Put in greased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat and cook until done.

title: "souper" chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soups, water and rice in pan.
Lay chicken on top; season and sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Cover tightly.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours until chicken is done and rice has absorbed most of liquid.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: jyaudz(meat dumplings)
directions: Salt meat to taste and mix with cabbage, sesame oil, green onions and ginger.
Mix well.
Place a teaspoon of mixture and place on wrappers.
Fold and seal by moistening the edges with water.
Have ready a large cooking pot, about 1/3 full of boiling water (with salt).
Place about 20 meat dumplings into pot of boiling water.
Continue boiling.
Water will foam.
When foam reaches top of pot, add 1/2 cup of cold water (repeat 3 times). Remove all dumplings from the water and repeat the cooking process until all have been cooked.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine rice (uncooked) with beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper, marjoram and 1/2 cup juice.
Mix lightly.
Shape mixture into balls (18).
Brown in skillet.
Add sugar to rest of juice.
Pour over meat.
Bring to boil for 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soy sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice, cornstarch, ginger, garlic and 1/4 cup of the reserved pineapple juice.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Add chicken and marinate at least 30 minutes.
Drain reserved marinade.
In a large skillet, heat oil and add chicken.
Cover and cook 7 to 10 minutes on each side. Add onions, pepper, pineapple chunks and 1/2 cup reserved marinade.
Cook 3 minutes more until chicken is no longer pink when cut into.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bran 'n molasses muffins
directions: Combine cereal, milk and molasses.
Let stand until most of the moisture is absorbed.
Melt butter. Combine egg and butter with the cereal mix and beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill greased muffin pan cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until muffins are lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: ambrosia(low-fat, low-cal)
directions: Mix fruit and sugar in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or up to 2 days.
Shortly before serving, sprinkle with coconut and cherries.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp and mushroom casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Add milk to mushroom liquid to make 3/4 cup.
In saucepan, cook onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender and mushrooms lightly browned.
Add soup, liquid, shrimp, half the cheese, 1 tablespoon parsley, pepper and cooked macaroni.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional chopped parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chilies con queso
directions: In a saucepan melt cheese over low heat.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients except tortilla chips in a small bowl; stir into melted cheese.
Serve in fondue pot or chafing dish with tortilla chips.
Makes 1 quart.

title: apple fiber oatmeal cookies
directions: It's so delicious and awful (wait until you read the ingredients!).
Thank goodness we were biking our way through the San Juan Islands when we found this recipe for a local delicacy at the tourist office in Nanaimo on Vancouver Island.

title: sauteed crab meat
directions: Remove
cartilage from crabmeat.
Melt butter in saucepan; saute
garlic
and green pepper until peppers are tender but not brown.
Add parsley, salt, pepper, Old Bay and brandy. Gently toss
in
crabmeat;
saute
slowly
until
crabmeat is heated,
5 to 8 minutes.
Serve on platter with parsley sprigs and lemon wedges, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Cook together hamburger, celery and onion.
Add all ingredients together in a greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: teriyaki pot roast
directions: Combine flour, garlic powder and pepper.
Coat both sides of meat with flour mixture; reserve mixture.
Lightly brown meat slowly on both sides in hot oil in Dutch oven or large skillet. Combine teriyaki sauce and 1 1/4 cups water; pour over meat.

title: mediterranean crescent pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray. Separate dough into 8 rectangles; place on lightly floured surface.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Press or roll each to form 8 x 5-inch rectangle.
Arrange 1/8 of Prosciutto slices evenly over each rectangle.
In small bowl, stir together cheese, pepper and oil.
Sprinkle with basil.
Starting at short side of each rectangle, roll up; seal long edges.
With serrated knife, cut each roll into 5 slices.
Place, cut side up, on cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Serve warm.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Boil raisins in water 5 minutes.
Add sugar mixed with cornstarch, spices, mustard and salt.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Stir in butter and vinegar.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 375°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chalupa
directions: Fry corn tortilla flat in hot oil.
Cover fried tortilla with cheese.
Put in oven until cheese is melted.
Top with lettuce, beans and tomatoes and serve hot.

title: cornbread and beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a 10 to 11-inch ovenproof skillet.

title: tater tot surprise
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan make layer of hamburger, then layer of Tater Tots.
Add soup mixed with 1 1/2 cans water.
Pour over meat and Tater Tots.
Cook for 1 hour at 375°.
Top with cheese; let melt and serve.

title: eggplant american casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, slice it, dip it in the mixed egg, then in the bread crumbs.
Fry them.
Let it drip on paper towel.

title: party punch
directions: Mix sugar and all juices together; chill.
Just before serving, add strawberries, sherbet and ginger ale.
A pint of unsweetened tea may be used as an extender.
Add extra sugar to taste.

title: seven flavored pound cake
directions: Combine butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Alternate flour and milk (add flavorings to milk).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or less.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Add glaze.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
This can also be heated in the microwave as a quick soup or put into soft taco shells with fixings.
Serves 4. Calories:
Fat:

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Beat Cool Whip and cheese.
Add crushed pineapple.
Stuff cookies with small slice on top.

title: zesty shrimp dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, chili sauce, lemon juice, onion and horseradish. Blend until mixed. Fold in shrimp.

title: ham loaf with mustard sauce
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan. Cream the sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time, until each is well blended.
Mix in extracts.
Beat in flour, salt and soda alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Slide sharp knife around edges of cake. Allow to cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Blend milk, 3 tablespoons shortening, sugar and milk. Cool to lukewarm by adding water. Add yeast and mix well. Add egg, then flour; mix until well blended. Place in bowl and brush with melted shortening. Let rise. Form into balls and bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes until brown. Easy and very tasty.

title: pizza
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast and 1 teaspoon salt. Add water and cooking oil.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
On floured surface, knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl. Turn once to grease top. Cover and let rise until double (1 hour).

title: plum jelly(sure-jell recipe)
directions: Combine plum juice and Sure-Jell in a large thick pot.
Cook to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Quickly add sugar. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim bubbles off the top with a large spoon.
Ladle into hot jars.
Seal and let cool.
Yields 9 cups of jelly!

title: french toast casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter, if desired.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In large utility dish put the cabbage, top with the soup, then the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Very simple but very good.

title: pot pie with herb crust
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread meat and vegetables in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Pour mixed soup and broth over all.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over all evenly. Bake 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese biscuit
directions: Grate cheese; cream and add Crisco.
Mix well; add dry ingredients to flour and mix by sifting well.
Roll dough very thin; cut in small biscuits.
Bake slowly to a light brown, or until done, not too brown, 325° for 25 minutes.
It makes about 125 biscuits.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear cake into chunks.
Mix strawberry gelatin and strawberries together.
Layer punch bowl, starting with cake, then strawberry mixture, then Cool Whip.
Layer these ingredients to make 2 or 3 layers, ending with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 1 or 2 hours.
Zero fat grams.

title: lamb chops with eggplant
directions: In 6-quart casserole, heat oil, add onion and garlic and cook until translucent; remove.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In an oblong pan, spray with Pam.
Spread with nuts, then coconut.
Mix cake as directed.
Pour over coconut.
Mix melted margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Pour over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake will crack across top.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt chocolate with Crisco in top of double boiler.
Beat in sugar and eggs. Then add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: black bottom cookies
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, egg and salt. Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips; set mixture aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with celery, onion, salt and pepper until tender. Remove skin, fat and bones and break into bite size pieces. Reserve 2 cups stock.
Spread chicken evenly in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass casserole.
Heat chicken and mushroom soups with 1 cup stock. Pour over chicken.
Mix margarine with 1 cup stock until margarine melts.
Add stuffing mix (less 1/3 cup) until fairly stiff.
Dab stuffing and margarine mix evenly over casserole mixture.
Sprinkle remainder of stuffing (dry) evenly over damp spots in casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: steak soup
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven. Add flour and mix into a roux. Carefully add water and bring to a boil to thicken.

title: creamy cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, covered, 10 minutes in a small amount of boiling salted water.
Drain well; set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons oleo in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add cabbage to white sauce, mixing well; spoon into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese; top with bread crumbs and drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the ingredients, except for the Feta cheese.
Cover in a tight lid bowl and chill at least 24 hours.
Shake bowl every couple of hours or open and stir ingredients.
One hour before serving, drain dressing from the bowl and add Feta cheese (reserve a couple of tablespoons for top).
Cover and chill.
When ready to serve, pour into serving bowl and garnish with remaining Feta cheese.
Warm pita breads add a special accompaniment to this colorful salad.

title: easy apple crisp(better than apple pie)
directions: Cut apples and put in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish or pan. Blend butter and sugar, then add cinnamon, flour and oats.
Spread mixture on top of apples.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water, then add Seven-Up and chill until partially set.
Then add drained crushed pineapple (save juice), miniature marshmallows and bananas to the chilled jello and set.

title: fast fixing chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Pour oil in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan,
Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan; stir with a fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread evenly in pan. Bake for 35 - 45 minutes until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Use a knife to loosen cake from sides.
Cut and serve directly from pan.
Delicious served with Cool Whip topping.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Chopped onion may be added.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon at a time into hot oil.
Delicious with fish.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham crumbs until all crumbs are moist.
Put half of the crumbs in bottom of pan.
Mix Dream Whip and milk until stiff.
Add sugar and cream cheese and mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour half of mixture over packed crumbs in pan.
Put pie filling over creamed mixture.
Pour remaining half of creamed mixture over pie filling and top with remaining half of graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry tiffany torte
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Gradually add 1/2 cup milk to softened cream cheese, mixing well until blended.
Add pudding mix, remaining milk and lemon juice; beat slowly for 1 minute.
Pour over crust; cover with strawberries.
Spread dessert mix over strawberries.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rotini pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to directions.
Drain.
Add cauliflower and broccoli to small amount boiling water and cook 1 to 2 minutes until tender-crisp or may use uncooked.
Combine all ingredients. Toss dressing with salad.
Cover and chill.
Toss gently before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Test stick with fork.
Cool.
Remove skins, mash and add remaining ingredients except peanuts.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Fold in chopped nuts.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour fruit and pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cake mix on top of fruit.
Microwave butter until melted. Pour butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until light brown.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Melt in skillet.
Add 2 packages midget wieners.
Simmer 20 minutes in skillet.
Keep warm in a crock-pot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan.
Top with tomato sauce or ketchup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until cooked through and bacon is cooked.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix in heavy 1-quart saucepan until blended the first 3 ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and sugar is dissolved.
Boil until candy reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper; quickly separate nuts into small pieces.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: potatoes in dill sauce
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in medium size pieces.
Cook in just enough salted boiling water to cover.
When potatoes are almost cooked, add flour which has been dissolved in half and half or cream.
Cook to thicken sauce, stirring occasionally.
Add dill. If sauce is too thick, add additional cream and continue to stir until desired consistency.
May add pepper to taste, if desired.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook and drain sausage and beef separately.
After draining beef and sausage, combine them and add grated cheese.
Cheese must melt and blend with meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on "party rye"; quick freeze on cookie sheets 10 to 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, put into 400° oven (frozen) for 15 minutes.
One recipe uses 1 1/2 loaves of rye.
Makes 48.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until it falls from the bone.
Grease bottom of flat casserole dish.
Line with the broccoli.
Place over the chicken.
Combine the mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice and soup to make a sauce.
Pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle over the cheese, then the bread crumbs.
Cook in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Roll in flour and brown.
Put into spaghetti sauce to cook.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Butter dish.
Place broccoli in casserole with cut up chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper in bowl and pour over top of chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine stuffing mix with melted oleo and sprinkle over top of cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
When doubling, bake 40 minutes.

title: teddy bear popcorn
directions: Combine cinnamon sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in popcorn.
Mix well.
Toss in grahams and M&M's.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand, ReaLemon brand and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill. Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add juices and banana.
Mix well and freeze in freezing containers.
Place frozen block into punch bowl and pour in ginger ale.
Punch will be slushy.
Serves 60.

title: meat balls (1)
directions: Soak bread crumbs in water, enough to wet them well.
Mix all together and form small meatballs.	Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form a ball. Roll in pecans (chopped).

title: red wine marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Soak steaks for an hour or so.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until tender; cool.
Coarsely grate potatoes.
In a small saucepan over low heat, almost melt butter or margarine and cheese.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, stirring lightly.
Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: red potatoes with garlic
directions: Cut potatoes into desired shape (diced) with skin on.
Place in Pyrex pan.
Add minced, fresh garlic to taste.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil water, sugar and syrup until they form a soft ball in cold water.
Pour slowly into the beaten egg whites.
Add nuts and vanilla and turn into pan.
When cool, cut into squares.
Can be dropped by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: dream squares or dream cake
directions: Mix together with hands; pat into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While baking crust, mix the filling.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook, cool and crumble corn bread.
Dice all other ingredients and toss with mayonnaise and sugar.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix orange juice following directions on can.
Combine orange juice and ginger ale and pour over sherbet.
Yields approximately 75 to 100 servings.

title: favorite lasagna
directions: Brown meats in a large skillet; drain well.
Return to medium heat and add seasonings, blending well into meats.
Add tomato paste and water, stir until sauce has thoroughly coated meat mixture.
Add tomato sauce and blend well.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes until thickened.

title: dublin fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, rum and orange extract and beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Stir flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Stir. Add mincemeat.
Stir in candy fruit.
Pour into heavily greased Bundt pan.
Bake cake at 300° to 325° for 2 1/2 hours or cupcake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup, salt, vinegar and vanilla. Cook until mixture forms a soft ball by testing in cold water.

title: brown bread
directions: Put baking soda and dates in bowl.
Cover with boiling water until other ingredients are mixed.
Cream butter, eggs and sugar together.
Add flour and date mixture alternately.
Beat well. Add nuts.
Grease sides of 2 large juice cans and fill 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice. Drain the fruit cocktail, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix with the cream mixture.
Add the chopped pecans and fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate and serve when firm. This pie can be frozen.
Take from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: In 4-quart dish over medium heat, cook meat until brown.
Add onion, carrot and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender, stirring.
Stir in soup, water and beans with their liquid.
Mix thyme, bay leaf and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in pasta.
Cook about 12 minutes more. Discard bay leaf.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and form into loaf.
Place in rectangular pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add 1 cup sugar and the Pet milk; mix well.
In separate small bowl, mix the cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add to egg mixture, then add the melted butter and vanilla.
Mix and pour into a deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Use bread that is not quite fresh, about 2 days old.
Cut the French bread into slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Beat milk, egg, salt, pepper and sugar together in a shallow bowl.
Heat a large heavy skillet.
Melt about 2 tablespoons butter or margarine. When fat is hot and sizzling, soak slices of bread in egg-milk mixture. Leave them in liquid until they are wet through, but do not fall apart.
Fry bread quickly until golden brown.

title: garden taco rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except the cheese.
Reduce heat to low and cook for about 15 minutes. Turn off heat.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand about 3 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar; mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla and mix again.
Form into rolls wrapped in plastic wrap and chill at least 1 hour.
Cut into 1/4 inch slices and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes.

title: clara jane's rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 2 quart casserole at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef stroganoff i
directions: Brown steak and onions in butter or margarine.	Stir in soup, water, sour cream and paprika.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir often.
Serve over noodles. Can freeze.
Serves 4.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat in oil.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, pepper, soy sauce and beef stock.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cut the vegetables.
When meat is almost cooked, add carrots, celery and onion.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Stir into stew and simmer a few minutes.
Good!
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple salad
directions: Dice unpeeled Red Delicious apples.
Thinly slice celery.
Add raisins to apples and celery.
Pour orange juice over all and mix well.
Set in refrigerator a couple of hours before serving.

title: velvet hammer("good milk shake")
directions: Mix in blender and freeze until ready to serve.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in
large saucepan. Add milk gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Bring to a bubbly boil on high heat, stirring continuously.
Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil, without stirring, until it reaches soft ball stage. Remove pan from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir. Allow to cool at room temperature.
Beat until it thickens and loses its gloss. Put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch lightly buttered pan.

title: colcannon
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the potatoes in boiling water, salted, for 30 to 40 minutes, or until tender.
While the potatoes are cooking, cook the cabbage in a saucepan in a small amount of boiling water for 5 to 7 minutes, or until tender, and drain very well.
Drain the potatoes well, then peel and mash them with enough of the milk to make a soft consistency.
Stir the cabbage into the potatoes, then season with salt and pepper.
Spoon the colcannon into a serving dish; make a hollow in the center and put the butter in the hollow to melt slowly into the mixture.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook whole box of jumbo shells by letting water boil first, pouring shells in and letting them boil for 10 minutes.
Mix together the remaining ingredients except the spaghetti sauce. Drain shells well using colander and stuff shells with mixture.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend until smooth and serve with a fruit platter.

title: peach butter
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine the peaches and orange juice. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and cook peaches in juice for 5 to 10 minutes until soft. In a blender, blend the peach mixture until smooth (you should have 1 1/2 cups puree).
Combine peach puree, orange peel, sugar, honey and allspice.
Bring to a full boil. Reduce heat and boil gently until it thickens.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: skillet green bean and noodle toss
directions: In skillet, cook garlic, rosemary and herb and spice seasoning in oil for 1 minute.
Drain beans (reserving liquid) into skillet.
Add tomatoes; bring to boil.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles; reduce heat.
Cover and cook about 18 minutes, adding beans during last 5 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding; fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, line bottom with graham crackers, then pudding, then crackers, remaining pudding, then last of crackers.
Spread crackers with frosting.
Refrigerate.

title: micro-chocolate pudding
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine 3 dry ingredients.
Gradually stir in skimmed milk.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring, until pudding is thick and boiling.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in serving dishes and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix in a blender until thick.
This makes approximately the same amount as a can of store bought sweetened condensed milk.

title: curry dip
directions: Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with sliced carrots and celery.
Decorate with paprika on top.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix together beef, onions, eggs, salt and pepper. Pat meat mixture into a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and drain off fat. Add potatoes and cheese. Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well. Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to the zucchini and egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine.
Mix well.
Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jacket.
Cool and dice.
Add celery, parsley, eggs (hard-cooked) and onion.
Fry bacon.
Combine beaten eggs, sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and vinegar diluted with water. Mix well.
Pour egg mixture into hot bacon and drippings.
Stir until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Pour over the potato mixture and mix lightly.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mom's school paste
directions: Dissolve flour and sugar in a little water.
Add boiling water and cook until transparent, like starch.
Add oil of cloves. Bottle for use.
Keep tightly closed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together	at low speed until well mixed. Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) or 3 (8 x 4-inch) greased and floured loaf pans.	Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls.
Pan-fry until brown in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Cook spaghetti and add your favorite spaghetti sauce with meat balls.

title: chinese beef and beans
directions: Slice steak diagonally into thin strips. Combine contents of gravy mix envelope, soy sauce, sugar and ginger. Pour over meat; toss lightly. Heat half of oil in large skillet. Add beans. Cook and stir 5 minutes until tender-crisp. Remove from skillet. Heat remaining oil in same skillet. Add steak. Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add beans and water. Cook, stirring until heated. Serve over hot rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except the flavoring in the top of double boiler.
Beat while cooking 7 minutes after the water boils.
Beat all the time.
Remove from stove and add the flavoring.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
The frosting should not be hot when put on cake.

title: cheese, ham and potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in rounds.
Cook about 8 minutes.
Don't overcook the potatoes.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour into greased glass dish (long one).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour into buttered 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is lightly browned.

title: peanut butter cookie kisses
directions: Mix together Crisco, brown sugar, peanut butter, salt and egg. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten by pressing crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cookies are removed from oven, immediately press a candy kiss into the center of each cookie.
Best when eaten warm.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat in layer pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange pineapple halves, cherries and pecans over sugar mixture.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half the batter* (about 2 1/2 cups) evenly over fruit in pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Invert at once onto serving plate.
Leave pan over cake a few minutes. Serve warm plain or with whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in heavy saucepan and bring to boil. Add hot dogs and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir periodically. Serve with toothpicks.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Mix bananas, orange juice and lemon juice in blender.
Transfer to large container; add sugar and water mixture and pineapple juice and blend well.
Freeze in 2 (1/2 gallon) large mouth plastic or paper cartons.
Remove from freezer a couple of hours before serving.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in a	mixing	bowl.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and condensed milk.
Mix well.	Add the mashed bananas and mix well at high speed.
Pour this mixture
into the freezer.
Add enough milk to reach the fill line on
the container.
Mix and freeze.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Cream eggs, margarine and sugar.
Add milk, then pineapple and bread cubes.
Grease casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sinfully chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour pan. Beat cake mix, pudding, butter eggs and spice blend in bowl on low speed 2 minutes scraping bowl occasionally. Pour into pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pan. Invert from pan onto cake plate. Cool 30 minutes. Prick top and side of warm cake with fork; spread chocolate topping over cake. Sprinkle with nuts. Cool completely about 1 hour. Store in cake taker.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Boil sugar, butter, syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir well; pour over popcorn in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Place in oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and chill.
Roll into a ball and then roll in chopped nuts.
Makes one small ball.
For a larger cheese ball, double or triple the recipe.

title: elephant stew
directions: Stew elephant into bite-size pieces.
This should take about two months.
Cover with brown gravy.
Cook over kerosene fire about four weeks at 465°.
This will serve about 3,800 people.
If more are expected, then 2 rabbits and 1 turkey may be added.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl and set aside the granulated sugar and flour.
Bring to a boil the margarine, shortening, cocoa and water.
Pour mixture into sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and salt.
Bake in 10 1/2 x 15-inch cookie sheet type jelly roll pan for 20 minutes at 400°.
About 5 minutes before cake is done, bring to boil the margarine, cocoa and milk. Remove from heat and add 1 box powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and nuts (optional).
Pour on hot cake and spread around.

title: french spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to pkg. directions; drain well, and set aside.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Put all ingredients into frying pan and simmer for about 1 hour.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Peel potatoes; put in cold water.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add evaporated milk.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Combine eggs in large bowl.
Beat until frothy.
Shred potatoes on medium shredder.
Place immediately in egg mix; turn to coat well.
Add parsley, 1 cup cheese and milk mixture.
Mix well. Turn into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add 1/2 cup cheese; continue to bake 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle
Brand
milk
and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and well
drained pineapple.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill before serving.

title: louisiana sausage and rice
directions: Microwave 500 to 700 W.
Place onion, celery and pepper in 2 1/2-quart oval glass-ceramic casserole dish.
Cover.
Microwave at High 4 minutes.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except cheese. Cover.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes more, stirring halfway through cooking.
Stir in cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jack straw tuna salad
directions: Combine carrots, celery, onion, tuna, Miracle Whip and mustard thinned with milk.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss in shoestring potatoes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: garbanzo and pasta salad
directions: Cook shells; drain and rinse in cold water.
In a large bowl, mix the
ingredients
for the dressing and let set for 5 minutes. Mix in the chickpeas and the cooked shells carefully so as not to mash them.	Cover and chill overnight.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; roll into ball.
Refrigerate; roll in nuts before serving.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: manicotti
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan.
Add garlic, onion and parsley; saute several minutes, stirring a few times, until garlic is golden.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 20 minutes.
While sauce is simmering, prepare meat filling.

title: turkey special
directions: Combine 3 cups stuffing with cooked broccoli, turkey, gravy and pepper.
Spoon into oblong baking dish. Top with remaining 1 cup stuffing. Bake in a 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar; let stand.
Put butter in a 2-quart casserole; place in a 325° oven to melt.
Combine remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon peaches on top of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: lamb stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add water until ingredients are slightly covered.
Turn crock-pot to low and cook 8 to 10 hours or cook 4 to 6 hours on high.

title: champagne punch(non-alcoholic)
directions: Mix together and chill.
Makes an elegant punch for a special occasion.

title: linguine with chicken
directions: Brown chicken and onion in butter, making sure chicken is thoroughly done.
Add mushrooms, garlic, cream or half and half, parsley, tomatoes, salt and peas.
Simmer until peas are soft. Cook linguine.
Top linguine with chicken mixture and Parmesan cheese.

title: southwestern game hens with spiced cornbread stuffing
directions: Season game hens with cumin, chili powder, salt and pepper. Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
In a medium bowl, mix together seasoning packet, 1/4 cup butter, 1 1/2 cups hot water, green chilies and onion.
Add stuffing mix.
Lightly stuff hens.
Place breast up on shallow baking sheet; brush with butter.
Roast, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover 1 hour. Baste occasionally.

title: orange loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure first 4 items together.
Add orange juice.
Add softened shortening and beat for 2 full minutes (by clock).
Add unbeaten eggs.
Continue to beat for 2 more minutes.
Scrape bowl sides and bottom frequently.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry hamburger and bacon together.
Dice up medium onion and add to the hamburger in the frypan.
Drain off excess grease from the frypan.
Open the cans of beans and put them in a slow cooker or crock-pot.
Add the hamburger combination to the beans in the slow cooker or crock-pot.
Add the catsup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar to the hamburger combination.
Mix well and cook for 1 hour on high and then simmer for an additional 2 hours on low heat or until ready to serve.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. For 1 cup of cocoa, place 1/4 cup of mix in hot water.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients in bowl just until mixed.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While cake bakes, make icing.
Simmer margarine, sugar and milk 5 minutes after reaching bubbly stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add coconut and nuts.
Mix in well.
Pour over cake when removed from oven.
Let cool before serving.

title: chinese-chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over wings and marinate overnight. Line pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn wings over and bake additional 30 minutes.
(I bake mine until brown.)

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces.
Cook according to package directions. Rinse with hot water.
Combine soup and milk in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add spaghetti, all but 2/3 cup cheese, turkey, mushrooms, onion, salt, pepper, pimento and black olives.
Toss gently.
Pour mixture into lightly greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add oatmeal and vanilla; mix quickly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets covered with waxed paper.
Cookies will be ready to eat in 1/2 hour.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all together and place into a greased ovenproof dish. Sprinkle with paprika and sliced almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Put ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and cherry into rectangular baking dish.
Dump cake mix and nuts on top.
Place pats of margarine on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: garlic green beans
directions: If fresh beans are used, cook in boiling water for 1 minute. Drain and add to other ingredients in saucepan.
Can be seasoned with bacon or ham, but are good without.
Add a little water to keep them moist.

title: swiss cheese and prosciutto toast
directions: In a food processor, combine Swiss cheese, egg yolk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and cayenne pepper until thoroughly mixed.
Remove top and bottom crust of bread (leave side crust); then slice bread horizontally 2 times leaving three horizontal slices.
On the bottom slice, spread 1/2 of cheese mixture; then top with 4 slices of Prosciutto.
Place middle bread layer on top and repeat with remaining cheese and Prosciutto.
Top with last bread slice.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water and set aside.
Dissolve sugar in pineapple syrup over low heat.
Add gelatin mixture to pineapple mixture and stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and grated cheese.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill for 1 hour or until firm.

title: cabbage bean soup
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Stir in salt, thyme, pepper, cabbage, tomatoes and broth or water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in beans.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until cabbage is done.
Great with cornbread!

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions.
Drain and lay in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with chicken.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spicy chicken bites
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Mix mustard and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Dip chicken pieces into mustard mixture and then into crushed crackers.
Place in baking pan and drizzle 1/4 cup butter over. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in casserole dish or pan.
Add squash, cut in chunks, diced pepper and onion.
(May use 1 or 2 peppers and 1 large onion.)
Add tomatoes and 1/2 to 1 cup rice, according to size of casserole.
Remember, rice swells and absorbs the liquid.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
I have given out this recipe many times.
It is well liked.

title: banana cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jack benny's chicken
directions: Cut chicken up and skin it.
Turn chicken pieces over in melted butter and then in bread crumbs that are seasoned with salt and pepper.
Put on a baking sheet.
Bake for 45 minutes at 450°. Pour the rest of the melted butter over it when done.

title: sleepy time drink
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Drink one hour before bedtime.

title: lemon puff pudding
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup of sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, rind and milk.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/2 cup sugar; fold into first mixture.
Pour into buttered baking dish; set in shallow pan of water 1-inch deep. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar together.
Pour into a punch bowl over ice.
Add chilled ginger ale.
Garnish with thin slices of lemon on top of punch.
(Orange slices can be used.)
Top slices with 1/2 cherry.
Yields about 6 quarts.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil and time for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add chocolate chips until melted; beat for about 15 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Beat for 10 minutes more.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9- inch pan.
Let cool and cut.
Yields 4 pounds.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well.
Put into individual crab shell shaped dishes or single serving dish and coat with additional mayonnaise (like a frosting), then sprinkle a little paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in a gallon glass jar. Add water with salt, enough water to cover pickles. Let stand at room temperature for 7 days; drain and rinse. Add alum with enough water to cover pickles and let stand 24 hours; drain and rinse. Boil vinegar, sugar and pickling spice. Pour over pickles, then add 1 cup sugar each day for the next 3 days. Do not refrigerate. Use right out of the jar.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Gradually mix in flour and 7-Up. Stir in lemon extract.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake in a preheated 325° oven until wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Layer chilies and part of cheese in a 9 x 13-inch buttered glass dish.
Beat other ingredients together and pour over the chilies.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: red lobster's cheese garlic biscuit
directions: Mix and brush over biscuits as soon as they come out of the oven and before you take them off the cookie sheet.
Serve warm. Yields about 2 dozen.

title: custard icing
directions: In a bowl, mix Crisco, oleo and sugar with a mixer until smooth.
Add flour mixture to sugar and Crisco and mix well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
This icing will freeze very well.

title: homestyle bread pudding
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine eggs with milk, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, bread, sugar and raisins. Pour into 1/2-quart baking dish. Place metal trivet or rack in bottom of slow cooker. Add 1/2 cup hot water. Set baking dish on rack. Cover pot; cook on high for about 2 hours. Serve pudding warm or cool.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mash dry Jell-O thoroughly into cream cheese.
When well blended, add 2 cups hot water and blend thoroughly.
Add can of pineapple including juice.
Finally stir in chilled 7-Up, sugar and vanilla.
Let stand in refrigerator until congealed.

title: tuna bean salad
directions: Mix lightly all ingredients except nuts.
Line serving bowl with salad greens and fill with mixture.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: casserole dish
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and part of fat from frypan.
Add onion and pepper to saute.
Add meat, soup and noodles.
Combine all ingredients except cheese, croutons and bacon in casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Add croutons and crumbled bacon.
Put in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: chocolate-covered banana pops
directions: Peel bananas.
Cut each into thirds.
Invert wooden stick into each banana piece.
Place on wax paper-covered tray.
Cover; freeze until firm.
In top of double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Remove bananas from freezer just before dipping.
Dip each piece into warm chocolate, covering completely, allow excess to drip off.
Immediately roll in peanuts.
Cover; return to freezer.
Serve frozen.
Makes 9 pops.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix all together.
Spoon onto jelly roll pan or cookie sheet; spread out.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chocolate chips or nuts optional.

title: hawaiian grilled pork chops
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Place chops in a large shallow dish.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, soy sauce, oil, onion, garlic and sugar, mixing well.
Pour over chops; cover and marinate in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Remove chops, reserving marinade.
Grill over medium coals, 40 to 45 minutes, turning frequently and basting with marinade.
Place a pineapple ring on each chop during last few minutes of cooking time. Yields 6 servings.

title: midget pizzas
directions: Cook sausage thoroughly and cut into thin slices. Roll each biscuit out in 4-inch diameter and place on baking sheet.
Spread each biscuit with tomato paste (is best).
Sprinkle with oregano and add pieces of sausage.
Sprinkle with plenty of cheese.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Grease bottom of baking pan.
Pour rice in.
Combine chicken soup and water and pour over rice.
Let stand a few minutes.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces and place on top of rice.
Pour remaining chicken soup over chicken.
Top with dry onion soup. Cover with lid or foil.
Place in oven at 350° and forget for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grilled pizzas
directions: Combine 2 cups biscuit mix and water, stirring to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a surface dusted with remaining biscuit mix; roll dough to coat and shape into a ball, kneading gently five times.
Divide into 4 equal portions; pat each portion into a 5-inch circle.
Cover grill rack with heavy-duty aluminum foil. Place circles on foil; cook over medium-hot (350° to 400°) for 8 minutes.
Turn over; top with pizza sauce, pepperoni and cheese. Cover with foil coated with cooking spray.
Cook for 10 to 12 minutes, or until edges are brown and cheese melts.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonsful onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 8-10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all other ingredients which have been mixed together.
Top with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
A 6 x 9 or 8 x 8-inch pan may be used. Makes 6 servings.

title: meat marinade(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Mix ingredients together, except meat tenderizer. Pour over meat. Marinate for at least 8 hours. Sprinkle with meat tenderizer frequently while marinating. Excellent on any kind of roast and steaks.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Stir in catsup and 3/4 teaspoon salt.

In bowl, prepare corn bread mix according to package directions. Spread half of the batter in a greased 8 x 8 x 12-inch baking pan. Spoon meat mixture over batter in pan; sprinkle with cheese. Spread remaining batter over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve topped with Mexican salsa.

title: sue's rhubarb cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread bottom with rhubarb.
Sprinkle on sugar.
Top with marshmallows.
Pour cake mix over marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix rice krispies, cheeses, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter.
Coat chicken with breading mix.
Grease, with butter, not Pam, a 13 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Sprinkle small amount of remaining coating in bottom of casserole.
Put chicken in dish, cover chicken with remaining coating.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fresh fish bake
directions: Place a slice of onion, lemon and butter in the body cavity of each fish.
Salt and pepper.
Fold tightly in foil
and cook over coals, about 10 minutes on each side (longer cooking time for larger fish).

title: honey carrot cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat egg and egg whites until light and frothy.
Beat in honey, butter and vanilla.

title: swamp cabbage stew
directions: Fry fatback, onions and chopped swamp cabbage until starting to brown. Add tomatoes, sugar, pepper and thyme.
Simmer until it thickens. Serve over rice.

title: karen's broccoli salad(makes a great side salad)
directions: Mix above ingredients in a large bowl.

title: complete meal casserole
directions: Brown the meat, onion and pepper in skillet and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sugarless fruit muffins
directions: Combine dates, raisins, prunes and water; bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine and salt; set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to fruit; stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Bake in miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
32 muffins.

title: almond puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into flour.
Sprinkle water over mixture; mix with fork.
Round into ball.
Divide in half on ungreased cookie sheet.
Set each half into a strip (12 x 3-inch) about 3-inches apart.
In a medium saucepan, heat 1/2 cup butter and water to boil.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in almond extract and flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs until smooth.
Divide in half and spread evenly over strips. Bake for 60 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until well set.

title: cherry torte
directions: Make Dream Whip like it says on the box, then put sugar in. Mix on low speed, then put cream cheese in slowly.
Pour over crust.
Put cherry pie filling on top.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Let cool. Add orange juice, water, pineapple, cherries and bananas.
Put in freezer.
Stir every hour until frozen so bananas don't go to the bottom.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Grease baking dish.
Sprinkle zucchini and tomatoes, onions and cheese in dish.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high.
Pour into dish.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Garnish with tomato slices if desired.

title: bubblin' party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in water (and set aside).
Combine pineapple juice and lemon juice and add this to the Jell-O mixture.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour the mixture into a punch bowl and add the sherbet and club soda.
Makes a great Halloween punch.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Simmer clams and lemon juice for 15 minutes.
Add 1/4 pound margarine; stir.
Then mix in remainder of ingredients.
Put mixture into small casserole dish and top with grated Parmesan or Romano cheese and paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: peanut butter buckeyes
directions: Cream the peanut butter and softened buttered well.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls and place on wax paper.
Chill overnight or 8 hours.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: corn meal dressing
directions: Bring to boil broth and margarine in a large tall pan.
Add enough corn meal to the consistency of corn bread.
Remove from heat.
Add onions, celery, bread crumbs, and eggs.
Mix well.
Add salt, pepper, sage, and poultry seasoning to taste.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix together in order given.
Drop by a teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add soups, Veg-All and cooked chicken (cut up) to a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix well. Add butter to stuffing.
Mix well and sprinkle on top. Bake in a 350° to 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: french apple pie
directions: Combine apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Turn into pie shell.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with topping (recipe follows).
Bake at 350° until apples are tender.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Prepare artichokes for cooking following basic direction. Drain water from artichokes.
Individually, hold each artichoke firmly in your hand and bang it upside down on a firm surface such as a countertop.
This causes the leaves to separate and the stuffing will be able to get down between the rows of leaves.
Bend and snap off the small bottom leaves and any outer leaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (seasoned to taste) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Drop in stick of margarine.
Debone chicken.
Reserve broth (2 cups). Pour broth, chicken, 2 cups rice, can of mushroom soup and asparagus into casserole dish.
Top with cheese (Mozzarella is good).
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: yellow squash pie
directions: Cook squash.
Drain well and mash.
Combine all ingredients. Spoon in pie shell.
Place strips on top, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm.

title: minted cantaloupe and fresh blueberries
directions: Combine water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add mint (chopped or bruised to bring out flavor).
Strain and chill.
Add to blueberries and cantaloupe.
Serve in sherbet glasses or bowls with a sprig of fresh mint.
Great on a hot evening for dessert.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, sour cream, soup, salt and pepper; stir well.
Set aside.
Melt butter; stir in stuffing.
Place half of stuffing in a buttered casserole dish.
Add the squash.
Top squash with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until lightly browned.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in salted water until almost done.
Layer in buttered casserole.
Top with cheese. Heat soup and milk; pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: date nut cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, baking powder, vanilla, salt and flour.
When mixed good, pour over dates and nuts, then mix well and put in a lined tube pan.
Press dough/batter down.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and melted butter.
Add milk, pineapple and crackers.
In 2-quart casserole, bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple juice; add mandarin oranges and bananas.
Stir.
Ready to serve.

title: marinated chicken kabob
directions: Stir dressing, orange juice and oil in large bowl.
Add chicken and vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Heat broiler or grill.
Arrange vegetables and chicken on skewers;
broil
or grill 3 inches from heat for 16 minutes or until
cooked
through, turning frequently.
Discard marinade. Makes 4 servings.

title: seafood surprise
directions: Melt butter in electric frying pan.
Set at 250°.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually; stir until smooth. Add milk gradually; stir until smooth.
Add Worcestershire and marjoram.
Continue cooking until thickened.
Add crab, shrimp, mushrooms and their liquid and olives.
Heat through (10 to 15 minutes).
Serve over the toasted English muffins; sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seafood salad
directions: Lightly butter bread on both sides.
Cut off crust.
Cut into cubes.
Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: frozen banana split pie
directions: Spoon 3 cups of topping into 9-inch pie plate.
Shape into shell; freeze.
Spread crust with 1/3 ice cream; top with pineapple.
Spread another 1/3 ice cream over pineapple, top with chocolate topping.
Spread remaining ice cream, freeze.
Before serving, top with bananas, topping, sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Makes 10 servings.

title: three fruit sherbet
directions: Combine fruit, juices, sugar and add fruit mixture to milk and cream.
Freeze.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup strawberries in small saucepan.
Add water, sugar, salt, cornstarch and drops of food coloring.
Bring to a boil slowly, stirring constantly, until thick and clear, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and wipe with paper towel.
In large bowl, combine sour cream, juice, sauce and seasoning.
Add chicken to this mixture, coating each piece well.
Next day, remove chicken from sour cream mixture.
Dip or roll in bread crumbs, coating evenly.
Arrange in single layer in shallow pan. Melt butter or margarine and spoon 1/2 over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°; spread rest of butter over and bake 15 minutes more until browned.

title: shirley's raw salad
directions: Grate cabbage and carrot.
Chop pepper and onion fine.
Mix well.
Make a dressing of vinegar, salad oil and sugar.
Mix well and let stand several hours or overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach; drain thoroughly and set aside.
Place soup mix and water in a small bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Let stand covered until vegetables are rehydrated.
Place cream cheese in large bowl. Microwave at 50% (medium) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until softened. Mix in rehydrated soup mix, spinach, sour cream and red pepper sauce.
Serve with toasted bread cubes, crackers or carrot sticks.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, oil and applesauce.
Mix.
Add pecans last.
Cook in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze with lemon juice and confectioners sugar.
Is very good without glaze.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter together. Add sugar; then add flour; then add 1 egg yolk at a time. Add vanilla. In a separate bowl, and with a separate mixer, beat egg whiles until stiff. Fold into mixture. Bake 1 hour 20 minutes at 325°.

title: mama's never fail fudge
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan. Add sugar, cocoa and milk. Let come to a good boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove and add flavoring. (Cook 1 minute for cake icing.) Beat candy with spoon until begins to thicken. Pour into buttered dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar, then eggs.
Mix and add all other ingredients.
Cook 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook meat and onion together until meat is browned.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, cumin powder and oregano.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors.
(The consistency should be like spaghetti sauce.
If it seems too dry, add either water or more tomato sauce.)
Using a separate bowl, mix chicken soup, sour cream and green chilies together; set aside.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish, begin layering ingredients, starting with the corn tortillas to cover the bottom of the pan.
Add half of the meat sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Add another layer of tortillas, then rest of the meat sauce and some cheese. Top with a final layer of tortillas.
Spread the soup mixture over the tortillas and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: super eggplant
directions: Remove stem, if skin seems tough, peel (otherwise, panfry with skin).
Cut into 1/2-inch to 1-inch slices or strips.
Dip in flour or dry bread crumbs or cracker crumbs.
Then dip into an egg beaten with milk.
Dip into flour or crumbs again.
Fry in hot fat (olive oil is especially good) until brown on one side.
Turn slices and brown on other side.
Sprinkle with salt and Parmesan cheese and serve piping hot.

title: cool veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread crescent roll dough on 13-inch round pizza pan and pinch seams together.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool completely.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, mixing well, and cook for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Combine last 4 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Bake in two well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes.
Keeps a long time.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, pound and cut steak into 1/4 inch wide strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika.
Allow to stand while preparing other ingredients. Using a large skillet, brown meat in butter, and garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Blend well and stir into meat mixture.
Cook stirring until clear and thickened about 2 minutes. Add tomatoes, stir gently.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream butter.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten lightly with fork. Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ground beef and rice skillet dinner
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Drop in rice.
Let come to a full boil.
Put lid on.
Turn heat to low, cook 25 minutes.
Chop pepper and onion.
Heat a large skillet.
Add oil and the chopped pepper and onion.
Turn heat to medium.
Cook and stir 2 minutes. Put lid on, cook 10 minutes.
Stir in ground beef and sprinkle beef bouillon powder over it.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate fruit dip
directions: Mix cocoa, orange juice concentrate and honey.
Slowly stir in chocolate milk.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Cool.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 onions.
Pour into 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Then top casserole with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water as directed on package.
Heat tomato soup until hot.
Combine the gelatine mixture with tomato soup.
Combine with remaining ingredients with the exception of the mayonnaise.
Line fish mold with mayonnaise and pour mix into mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with crackers.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Chop the oysters.
Make a batter of the eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir the oysters into batter and drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat.
Turn the fritters over so that they may brown nicely on both sides.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix flour, salt and butter together until smooth,
then
stir
in
hot milk.	Slowly	add
mashed
cooked spinach to this.
Beat egg yolks until light and creamy and add to mixture.
Then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into buttered
baking dish.
Substitute chicken broth
for
milk
in white sauce for variety.
Bake at 350° for 25
to
minutes. Serve immediately.	Serves 4.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef well; drain off excess grease.
Put all ingredients in pan; stir well.
Cover and heat until cheese is fully melted.
Serve while warm with tortilla or corn chips.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in the dressing mix.
Bake with skin side up at 325° for 45 minutes, until brown and crispy.

title: cheesy baked onions
directions: Slice onion thin and separate into rings and put in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt butter; stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Gradually add milk; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook and stir for two minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Pour over onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until onion is tender and cheese melts and browns.
Yield: 4 servings. (Can be halved.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: When recipe calls for squares of chocolate, you may use 3 tablespoons cocoa plus 1 tablespoon butter for each square.
Melt together before adding to recipe.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Fry meat and onion together; season.
Add catsup and soup and heat thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish and top with cheese slices.
Top cheese slices with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Add broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks. In large plastic bag, add all ingredients. Close bag and shake until well coated. Empty potatoes into shallow baking dish. Bake 40 minutes at 450°, stirring occasionally. Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley. Yield: 8 servings.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: lynn's favorite pizza pockets
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Press biscuit to form a 5 inch circle and place on a greased cookie sheet. Spread 1-2 Tbsp. of sauce on only half of the circle, careful not to spread too close to edge. Add fillings of your choice. Fold the pizza circle in half. Press the edges with a fork to seal. Bake for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown chops in fat over medium
heat at 325°.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Remove
chops
and
saute
mushrooms,
celery and onions in butter
over
medium heat at 250° until tender.
Add bouillon cubes; crush
and stir to dissolve.
Add cooked rice, cream and remaining
1/4 teaspoon salt.
Place rice mixture in 11 x 7-inch baking
dish, arranging chops on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated vegie salad
directions: Cut up vegies into bite size pieces.
Mix up dressing and pour over the vegetables.
Marinate the vegies overnight, stirring often.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine egg, turkey and stuffing. Mix with 3/4 can of gravy. Place in loaf pan and top with remaining gravy. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian meringue
directions: Combine water and sugar in a small saucepan.
Cook until it reaches 238 on a candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites to form soft peaks.
Continue beating and slowly pour syrup into egg whites. Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Bake at 425 degrees until brown.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water for 45 minutes.
Remove.
Boil spaghetti noodles in the same water.
Mix and saute onions, celery and peppers.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place in oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, onions and raisins in large salad bowl.

title: hoppin john
directions: Combine peas and water.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand one hour.
Add ham hocks, onion, chili pepper and salt.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until ham and peas are tender.
Remove ham hocks. Cut meat into small pieces, discarding bone and rind.
Drain peas, reserving liquid.
Add water to reserved liquid to make 3 cups.
Return peas, liquid and ham to kettle; add rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt to lukewarm
the
brown sugar and shortening.
Add egg, flour, vanilla and	nuts.
Mix well and pour into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: In a large frying pan, melt butter.
Cook onion until tender. Remove.
Brown meat; remove.
To drippings in frying pan, add flour, salt, and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in buttermilk.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Add mushrooms and parsley.
In a butter casserole dish, layer potatoes then onion and steaks.
Pour sauce over all. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.
Enjoy.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt butter in glass casserole. Mix batter: flour, sugar and milk. Pour batter over butter. DO NOT STIR.
Spoon fruit over batter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar. Bake at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Add Italian dressing and marinate for 8 hours in refrigerator.
