Remove chicken; add apricot preserves to Italian dressing (that was used as marinade).
Return chicken to marinade mixture and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Good served with rice.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Toss broccoli, white cheese, onion, basil leaves, salt and pepper and spoon in 9-inch deep pie shell.
Mix cornstarch, milk and eggs and pour over ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos(serves 10)
directions: Layer in flat, 9 x 12-inch or larger dish.
Open chilies and lay flat to cover casserole dish.
Add 1/2 of each cheese.
Repeat chilies and cheese (2 layers).
Mix flour and yolks, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend egg whites with flour mixture gently.
Pour flour and egg mixture over the top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce or salsa over the top (with additional chopped chilies, if desired) and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup and sour cream together.
Spread in 9 x 18-inch pan.
Pick the chicken off the bone and spread on top. Combine water and butter; heat.
Add to stuffing mix.
(You may make your own with Pepperidge Farm stuffing, onions and celery.) Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and flour.
Spread in greased 10 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix rest of the ingredients together and spread over mix in pan.
Bake 20 minutes. Cut in squares. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and syrup in a 2-quart measuring cup.
Bring to a boil in the microwave (approximately 3 minutes). Stir and add peanuts and return to the oven and cook for 8 minutes.
Remove and add butter, vanilla and color.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet and cool.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Grease and flour a 2-inch deep long baking pan.
Preheat oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy eclair dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch dish with crackers.
Layer pudding 3 times, 2 times with crackers.
Top with frosting.

title: baked rice
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart baking dish.
(Corningware dish works well.)
Add uncooked rice.
Blend well (using a spoon).
Add other ingredients.
Blend well.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour; brown in oleo.
Remove chicken; stir in butter, soup water and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Spread uncooked rice into shallow baking dish.
Pour all but 1/3 cup of mixture over rice.
Add chicken and the rest of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: corn dogs batter
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Dip hot dogs into batter to coat.
Fry in deep fat at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels after removing from fat.
Serve with condiments as desired.

title: gooey rich dessert
directions: Mix first
four
ingredients, like pie dough.
Pat onto cookie sheet.
Bake
minutes
at
or
until browned. Crumble with fork,	while still hot.
Put half the crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan
and
add
half the nuts.
Drizzle crumbs with half a jar
of caramel syrup.
Cover with ice cream.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs, nuts and
syrup on top.
Freeze 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute onion and pepper in Pam.
Add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 4 minutes.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add chicken, mushrooms and peas.
Mix.
Add vermicelli, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in Pam sprayed casserole and heat at 350° until bubbly.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet.
Saute the bell pepper and onion until soft but not browned.
Add the ground beef and brown. Drain well.
Stir in the rice, tomato sauce, and water.
Cover and cook over low heat about 8 to 10 minutes or until the rice has absorbed the liquid. Season with salt and black pepper to taste.

title: mustard honey chicken bake
directions: Stir together mustard and honey.
Dip chicken pieces in mustard mixture, then in crumbs.
Arrange on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender, turning once after 20 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Mix cider and sugar in a crock-pot.
Place allspice, cloves and cinnamon in a basket.
Brew.
Remove basket and serve.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Heat milk and rice in heavy saucepan at about medium-high until heated through.
Lower heat to simmer and cook until thickens.
This should take over an hour.
Stir occasionally from the bottom.
Remove from heat and add sugar and vanilla.
Serve with cinnamon, if desired.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Set aside.

title: crab and shrimp with almonds
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate.
When ready to bake, fold in noodles; top with almonds and bake at 375°, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until piping hot.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in olive oil.
Add onion and garlic. Cook until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil, oregano, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Stir in olives.

title: angels delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in a double boiler.
Cool in refrigerator.
Beat whipping cream until stiff and fold into marshmallow mixture.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Line casserole bottom with graham cracker crumbs.
Fill with creamy mixture and place more graham cracker crumbs on top of mixture.
Best if made 24 hours in advance of party.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Cook blueberries 10 minutes.
Mix together cornstarch and sugar and then add to berries.
Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: fish and vegetable chowder
directions: Cook bacon in a large pan over medium heat; remove bits and reserve.
Saute onions, garlic and celery in bacon drippings, stirring often, until the onions are light yellow; about 15 minutes.
Add potatoes, 1 cup water, salt, bay leaf and thyme. Simmer covered for about 20 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender.
Add fish, vegetables and remaining water.
Simmer for 10 to 12 minutes longer or until fish is cooked.
Add cream and milk; heat just to boiling.
Serve with bacon bits.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: turkey tomorrow
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Mix turkey, eggs, celery and onion, then add soup mixture. Stir to blend.
Add the crushed chips.
Put in shallow casserole. Top with another cup of crushed chips.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix in the vegetables (chopped or grated), as much or as little as desired.
It's a pretty salad, as well as delicious and nutritious.

title: super nachos
directions: Spread tortilla chips about one layer dip.
In a skillet, cook sausage until brown, then drain off fat.
Sprinkle sausage over tortilla chips.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.

title: scalloped tomato casserole
directions: Layer half each of tomatoes, onions, cracker crumbs, sugar and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat with remaining half. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Spread sour cream on top; sprinkle croutons on sour cream.
Spoon melted butter on top of croutons. Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peach crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients except peaches to form crumbs.
Dice fruit in baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Put crumbs over fruit and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until well brown on top.

title: cornish game hens
directions: Stuff the birds and baste with sauce.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes; rinse.
Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover 5 minutes; drain.
Cook and stir hamburger and onion in 10-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in salt, garlic salt, rice and 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Heat through. Stuff each pepper with hamburger mixture.
Stand upright into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cook covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: tut's toffee
directions: Place Saltines in single layer on foil lined jelly roll pan. Combine brown sugar and butter in microwave safe bowl. Microwave on high power for four minutes. Stir. Pour over Saltines. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top. Return to oven just until chips are shiny. Remove from oven and spread over Saltines. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Chill overnight, break into bite sized pieces.

title: beer cheese
directions: Cut the Velveeta and Cheddar into small chunks and place in food processor.
Let come to room temperature.
Add all other ingredients except the beer.
Start processor and slowly add the beer.
Process until mixture is smooth.
Let set overnight in refrigerator or until the dried onions absorb the liquid in the mix.
Serve as a dip with crackers or any raw vegetable.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix everything but flour tortillas together.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Chill at least 1 hour. Slice in 1/2-inch slices.

title: southern iced tea
directions: Boil sugar, water, and lemon juice on high.
Remove from heat.
Drop tea bags into boiled mixture.
Cover and let steep 20 minutes.

title: roast with brown gravy
directions: Cook all (except gravy mix) in crock-pot all day on high. Remove roast and vegetables.
Add brown gravy mix (3 tablespoons for every cup of water).

title: spring poppy seed salad
directions: Blend sugar, vinegar, salt, dry mustard and grated onion. Slowly beat in salad oil and poppy seed.
Pour over vegetables and toss.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread with salad dressing and dot with 1 tablespoon butter and caraway seeds. Top with corned beef and cheese. Spread crumbs on top. Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: fake rumaki
directions: You will also need round toothpicks.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of onions. Pour beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour milk mixture over beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove after 20 minutes and garnish with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes, just to brown.

title: orange walnut pie
directions: Cut orange into quarters, removing white pith in center.
Chop fine in blender.
Combine orange, sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and stir in butter. Cool slightly and mix in eggs.
Add walnuts and cinnamon and mix well.
Turn into pie shell and place pan on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until puffed up and firm.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: best fruitcake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Mix with diced fruit and nuts.
Beat eggs and add with melted butter and flavorings to fruit and nuts. Stir in large baking pan until well mixed.

title: pumpkin ice cream
directions: Stir the sugar, spices and pumpkin into the softened ice cream.
Mix until well combined.
Freeze until firm.

title: meringue brownies
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Beat 2 egg whites and add 1 cup brown sugar to make meringue.
Spread meringue over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: In large pot, soak peas in 2-quarts water overnight.
Bring to boil in same water, reduce heat and add hambone and peppercorns. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add vegetables and simmer an additional hour.
Remove hambone, cut meat from it, discard bone and chop meat finely.
Press soup through food mill.
Add chopped ham, milk, bouillon and frankfurters or sausage and simmer 20 minutes.
Add salt, if necessary.
Serves 10.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and egg.
Shape into 4 oval patties; brown in skillet for about 10 minutes.
Add onion, broth and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove patties.
Heat liquid to boil.
Mix cornstarch with small amount of water.
Stir into boiling liquid.
Boil for 1 minute.
Serve over patties.

title: corinne's egg pie
directions: Cream together the margarine, flour, Pet milk, sugar, egg yolks and rum (if desired).
Bake at 350° in a 9-inch or 9 5/8-inch prepared deep pie shell for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Cut up celery.
Add peas.
Add chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Stir in salt, pepper and Miracle Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, lemon juice, milk, melted butter and garlic salt.
Add crabmeat; mix thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: reese's peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Stir in chips.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool on rack.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Process on low speed for 30 seconds.
With blender on high, gradually add oil in a slow steady stream.
Blend about 30 seconds or until thickened.
Stir in poppy seed.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.
Serve on fruit salad.

title: microwave stuffed potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until tender.
In frying pan, saute onions in margarine; add mushroom slices.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, scoop out potato leaving the shell.
You'll need this later.

title: party salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk and refrigerate 1 hour. Stir in rest of ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Stir before using each time.

title: wassail
directions: This is delicious.
Put it in your crock-pot on high for 1 hour and then on medium for 3 to 4 more hours.
This is great for Christmas or New Years or when you're just plain cold.

title: do ahead sausage fondue
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Cut sausage into 1-inch chunks, brown, drain, then place on cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and dry mustard. Pour over sausage, cheese and bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Next day, dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over casserole. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours until set.
Serves 8.
Delicious.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop on cookie sheet with a spoon and bake in hot oven until done.
Put powdered sugar icing on top.

title: hot butter rum sauce(excellent on hot apple pie ala mode)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and milk in a 4-cup glass bowl.
Add butter.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes until mixture boils hard for 2 minutes and is thick.
Add rum.
Stir.
Can be made ahead and reheated in the microwave just before serving.

title: crunchy bars
directions: Melt chocolate and pour over the other mixed ingredients.
Pour onto wax paper.
Press out with your hand or a spatula.
Let this get cold.
Break into pieces.
Stores good in a plastic Baggie or airtight container.

title: original ranch cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese, beef and dressing; shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: split pea and tomato soup
directions: Mix soups and milk thoroughly.
Heat to boiling stage but do not boil.
Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Rinse the cabbage in cold water.
In a large stockpot, saute the bacon, onions and garlic in the oil for 5 to 7 minutes or until the onion is soft.
Add the chicken broth and tomatoes. When the broth begins to boil, add the cabbage and pepper.
Cook, covered, over high heat for about 5 minutes.
Lower to a medium boil for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add the potatoes and thyme and continue cooking at medium boil for 30 to 35 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Add more water if necessary. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter candies
directions: Mix well, using pastry blender first, then hands.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Dip into chocolate dip and place on waxed paper to harden.

title: maryland eastern shore white potato pie
directions: Bring to a boil water, salt, milk and butter.
Add instant potatoes, eggs, sugar, lemon and vanilla extract.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: bavarian inn ranch dressing
directions: Mix by hand and refrigerate.
Will keep for months refrigerated in jars with secure lids.
Makes 2 quarts plus.

title: baked pork chops and apples
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and place in large casserole. After removing pork chops, add 1/3 cup sour cream to pan and stir until mixed with browning from chops.
Meanwhile, cut and core 1 apple.
Place each half (open side up) on a pork chop.
Fill each half apple with 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Pour sour cream sauce over apples and pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serve with rice or egg noodles.
Quick, easy and delicious! Serves 2.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Process all ingredients in blender or food processor. Refrigerate.
Make ahead to enhance flavor.
Cucumber may be substituted for zucchini.
Serves 4.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Drain water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Fold all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender.
Cool and peel potatoes. Slice them crossways into circles and place in large Corning Ware dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
During last 5 minutes, can add Durkee French fried onion rings to top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and cut up yellow squash and onion; steam in tiny amount of water until just wilted.
Put in bowl and mash up.
Add melted butter and a beaten egg or two.
Mix and season well; pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with buttered saltine cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until browned.
Increase according to family size.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Make a paste of lemon juice and cocoa, add to flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and coloring. Mix well.
Bake at 350°.

title: preacher pie
directions: Press nuts in pie shells.
Bake at 350° until browned, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: casserole for leftover turkey
directions: Layer turkey on bottom of casserole dish.
Add soup and milk. Layer Mozzarella cheese.
Then layer on stuffing (Stove Top; do as box directions say).
Cover and place in oven.
Heat for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.
Then add rolls and veggies/salad.

title: pie meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in a saucepan.
Add boiling water.
Cook, stirring, until clear and thickened.
Let stand until cold.
Beat egg whites until foamy with mixer at high speed. Gradually add sugar and beat until thick.
With mixer at low speed, add salt, vanilla and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Turn mixer to high speed and beat until you can form stiff peaks.
Spread over cooled pie filling and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: celery amandine
directions: Cook, covered, over low heat the celery, butter and seasoning.
Add onion while it simmers.
When tender, remove and blend in flour. Add cream and bouillon; cook until sauce thickens. Just before serving, add almonds which have been lightly browned in butter.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown both sides of chops in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange chops in a single layer in a shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry 1 pound hamburg with onion.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Add flour, salt, chili powder, tomatoes and beef stock.
Cook until thick and smooth for sauce.
Fry corn tortillas until soft and warm.
Spoon meat into tortillas.
Roll and lay in baking dish.
Spoon sauce on top of tortillas.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sorghum and sugar to hard stage (hard ball).
Add soda. Pour over popped corn and mix.
Shape into balls (oil hands lightly to shape).

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put butter, fruit and sugar (if needed) and the cup of liquid in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Heat until butter is melted.
Mix flour and sugar; mix in milk, stirring until smooth.
Pour batter evenly over fruit mixture.
(Batter usually goes to bottom but rises while cooking.)
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
It's great with scoop of vanilla ice cream on top.
Suitable for freezing.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Add chips, cheese and dressing at serving time.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Put 1/2 crumbs in ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
To remaining crumb mixture, add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and set aside.
Cook zucchini in lemon juice until tender.
Then add sugar, nutmeg and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Simmer 1 minute, then add 1/2 cup crumb mixture until thickened.
Cool.
Place cool mixture in baked crust. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over filling.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon freeze pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze for 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter, syrup and cream.
Stir in vanilla, brandy and pecans.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set and pastry is golden brown.
Cool.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix ingredients and put in the refrigerator overnight. Shape into 2 rolls. Put on rack and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Turn over and bake another 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line bottoms of three 9-inch round cake pans with waxed paper. Microwave chocolate and water in large microwavable bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: cheese ball or roll
directions: Mix thoroughly the 3 cheeses.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add pecans.
Either roll about the size of Ritz crackers or make into a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate to harden (can freeze).

title: bean, hominy, rice salad
directions: Cook rice and cool; drain if necessary.
Saute green pepper and oil in nonstick skillet or spray with vegetable spray until tender.
Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix.
Keep in cool refrigerator.

title: gumbo la pontchartraine
directions: Cut chicken into serving portions.
Dredge lightly in flour. Saute in the melted shortening until brown.
Add onions and celery, cooking until soft.
Add all other ingredients except the okra and oysters.
Cook until the chicken is tender.
Add okra and oysters. Cook an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: potato frittata
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Layer half of the potato, onion and bell pepper slices in the skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat layering and seasoning.
Cover and cook until potato and vegetables are tender, stirring and turning frequently with a spatula, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with the thyme and remove from burner.
Set aside, leaving in the skillet.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, reserved liquid, thawed strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberry halves.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Toast pecans in a 325° oven for 15 minutes, until light brown. Beat egg whites; fold in sugar and salt.
Fold pecans into meringue.
Melt margarine in a jelly roll pan; spread pecans into margarine.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths; mix sugar and cinnamon.
Coat each biscuit well.
(Use bowl or bag.)
Mix brown sugar and margarine; heat until hot.
Put 1/2 of the biscuit pieces into a greased Bundt pan or tube pan.
Pour 1/2 of the syrup over; add 1/2 nuts, coconut and raisins.
Then add the rest of biscuit pieces, nuts, etc.
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.
If you use a tube pan, place on a cookie sheet to bake.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together, except margarine.
If mixture seems too dry, add a little more milk.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Cut margarine over the top.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.
Should be lightly browned.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim all fat from steak.
Cut into bite-size cubes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Cook steak and onion slowly until done.
Add soup; heat until hot and bubbly.
Meanwhile, prepare egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain and add to steak mixture. Add sour cream and serve.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Layer Twinkies in a pan with cream sides up.
Mix pudding as directed; then beat in cream cheese.
Pour mixture over Twinkies. Over this, spread Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: *Egg product may be used in place of whole egg.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Skin chicken and boil; when chicken is done, take out of broth.
Put rice into the boiling broth.

title: sausage-cream cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll 1 can of crescent rolls onto a greased cookie sheet, being careful not to separate dough.
Press into an 8 x 13-inch rectangle.
Using a second cookie sheet, repeat for remaining can of rolls.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: deviled clams
directions: Grind alternately the clams and slices of bread.
Saute in butter the onion.
Add flour, cream, pepper, poultry seasoning and celery seed.
Combine the two mixtures.
Moisten with a little clam juice if needed.
Simmer 5 minutes; fill shells.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.

title: juice juicer
directions: Mix juices together and chill.
Add 2 liter drink just before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mash bananas with a fork and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add bananas to creamed mixture with all other ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in greased muffin tin in 325° oven about 25 minutes or until done.

title: steak-umm delight
directions: Put the slices of Steak-umm on microwavable plate.
Place in microwave for 1 minute.
Take out; chop up meat.
Add hot sauce and meat softener.
Put back in for 8 minutes.
Take out and mix up. Put in for 1 more minute.
Take out and mix up.
Keep repeating process until all red meat has turned brown.

title: quick homemade raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray 9x5-inch loaf pan with non-stick spray.
Dust lightly with flour.
Combine raisins and water; set aside for 30 minutes.
Combine flour, baking soda, sugar substitute, cinnamon and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add raisins with liquid, egg, vanilla and oil.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown and firm to the touch.
Let stand 5 minutes; remove to cooling rack.
Serve warm or slice and toast.

title: easy apple dip
directions: Make day before serving.
Mix cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until it becomes smooth. Place in refrigerator overnight. Slice fruit and soak in lemon juice or salt to prevent discoloration.
Arrange and serve.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook flour, vinegar, sugar, egg and pineapple juice until thick, stirring constantly. Refrigerate while peeling and dicing apples. Fold all ingredients together and let set for at least 1 day.

title: pizza dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add sour cream, oregano and garlic powder; spread in 9-inch pie plate.
Spread sauce, then a layer of peppers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; remove and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips!

title: frosted brownie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl with mixer.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch round pans (2 of them) or 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: vi's cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Add cabbage; marinate 3 to 4 hours.

title: apple-cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the flour, sugar, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and melted margarine together until well blended.
Fold in the apples.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, until done.
Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon on top, if desired.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Make in layers- Bacos on top. Refrigerate.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Melt yeast in hot water.
Add rest of box.
Mix and roll out to pizza size.
Slice pepperoni and layer slices with slices of Mozzarella and spread on dough.
Roll and shape like horseshoe. Brush with beaten egg yolk.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400° and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa ala carbonara(egg and bacon sauce over pasta)
directions: Fry bacon in oil until crisp; drain.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper; add cream and cheese.
Cook pasta in salted, boiling water. Drain.
Preheat saucepan; add noodles.
Pour in egg and cream mixture; toss to coat.
Add bacon.
Continue to toss until mixture thickens.
Top with green onion or parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle more corn flakes on top and pour an additional 1/4 cup butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until top begins to brown.

title: crock-pot bean soup("nine bean soup")
directions: Rinse 2 cups bean mix.
Place beans in slow cooker. Cover with water 2-inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans. Add the water and next 4 ingredients. Cook on high in slow cooker for 1 hour.
Reduce to low and cook for 6 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Pour the boiling water over the bulghur in a large bowl. Cover the bowl; let stand 2 hours.
Drain off any excess water from the bowl.
Add the cucumbers, radishes, mint, olive oil, onions, lemon juice, salt and pepper to the bulghur.
Toss the mixture until all the ingredients are thoroughly blended. Refrigerate the tabbouleh salad until ready to serve.

title: cottage cheese roast
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in medium casserole which was sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: rhubarb slush
directions: In a small saucepan, combine rhubarb, water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
Cool for about 30 minutes.
In a food processor or blender, puree mixture, half at a time.
Stir in apple juice and lemonade.
Pour into a freezer container; cover and freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 45 minutes before serving.
For individual servings, scoop 1/3 cup into a glass and fill with soda.
To serve a group, place all of mixture in a large pitcher or punch bowl; add soda and stir. Serve immediately.
Serves 10.

title: tomato onion quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together except meat and cheese; pour in greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle meat and cheese on top and press gently under surface with spoon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: candied carrots
directions: Bring water to a boil in large skillet; add carrots, cinnamon, cumin and ginger.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add honey and lemon juice; bring to a boil.
Boil, uncovered for 4 minutes or until liquid evaporates and carrots are tender.

title: pumpkin chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and butter with mixer. Add remaining ingredients, except crust and whipped cream; blend well.
Pour mixture into prepared crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Good served with whipped cream.

title: cheese-stuffed burgers
directions: In a bowl, mix the ground beef, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll into 8 patties.
Top 4 of the patties with the cheese mixture and top them with the other 4 patties. Seal the edges tightly and broil.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries according to directions on package.
Add sugar and jello.
Stir well until jello is mixed.
Add pineapple and applesauce.
Cool in refrigerator until serving time.

title: quick and easy tamale pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Add garlic and onion; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, corn, water, chili powder, cumin and salt. Stir while slowly adding cornmeal.
Cook until thick.
Add olives and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 easily.

title: lizzy's chicken salad
directions: Boil and cool chicken; remove from bone and chop.
Place in large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients and toss to mix.
Cover and refrigerate approximately 2 hours before serving.
Great in sandwiches, too!

title: frito pie
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with 1 1/2 cups Fritos. Sprinkle onion evenly over Fritos. Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Pour heated chili on top and cover with another layer of Fritos and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients and allow to get cold.
Mix vegetables and pour dressing over them.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.
Overnight is fine.
Stir well and drain before serving.
Save liquid.
Marinate leftovers.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Add tomato puree to beef broth.
Set aside.
Peel and dice carrot, onion and celery.
Shred cabbage.
Combine these together. Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Do not drain.
Add to the beef broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste and 1 heaping spoonful of parsley flakes.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: trifle cake
directions: Soak angel food cake in rum or sherry flavoring (slice).
Line glass bowl with layer of cake, then prepared custard and pie filling.
Put fruit slices around side.
Repeat layers to top of bowl.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Decorate with fruit slices.

title: italian bread
directions: In a large bowl combine 2 cups of flour, yeast and salt.
Add 2 cups water.
Beat with electric mixer on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on High 3 minutes.
Stir in as much remaining flour as you can. Knead in enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough (8 to 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl.
Cover, let rise in warm place until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Divide in half. Cover; let rise 10 minutes.
Grease baking sheet (cookie pan). Roll into long loaves.
Brush with egg whites and water.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Brush with whites and put onion powder and cornmeal on top of loaves.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party rye
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, soup and chopped pepperoni. Spread on rye. Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees or until hot.

title: s.o.s.
directions: Brown hamburg in large skillet (crumble).
Season with onion salt, garlic salt, salt and pepper and Accent.
In large pot, bring to slow boil, milk, butter and mustard.
Add the hamburg; bring to slow boil.
Add water and flour mixture to the large pot until desired thickness.
Serve over toast.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put 1 cup rice in large Dutch oven (4 quart stainless steel kettle with lid).
Cover with 1/2-inch water.
Start on high.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Bring to a boil and add milk.
Turn to medium.
When boils, turn to low and add raisins (optional).
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Remove and let sit off the burner 20 minutes, covered.
Mix together the eggs, 1/2 cup water, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add to mixture and bring to a boil.
Put into serving dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired, before serving.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix flour, pepper and salt in plastic bag.
Coat chicken with mixture; reserve remaining flour.
In skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium heat.
Brown chicken 5 minutes.
Add remaining oil.
Turn chicken brown 5 minutes.
Remove and set aside.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Beat egg in 1-cup measuring cup.
Add milk to make 1 cup.
Mix dry ingredients with lard, then add egg and milk.
Use hands to mix more.
Makes 3 double crust, 10-inch pies and 1 single.
Can be refrigerated.

title: mom's chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine thoroughly. Mix all other ingredients well. Add to sugar and margarine mixture. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: quick onion rice
directions: In saucepan, combine soup mix and water; heat to boiling. stir in rice; reduce heat.
Cover; cook 20 minutes until rice is tender.

title: pork chops and wild rice
directions: Mix rice (and spices), soup and water in a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Add Chinese vegetables and mushrooms.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: souper meat 'n potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes; top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more or until done.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips or corn flakes very well and spread evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with crushed chips or corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or 45 minutes if using a glass pan. You can make this a day before if you add the chips right before baking.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients, then add eggs, sherry or rum and pumpkin and mix well. Add nuts and stir in. Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans or 4 small pans. Bake large pans 45 minutes to 1 hour or small pans 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cook squash for 10 minutes; drain and mash.
Add beaten egg and onion to squash.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix with the squash mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over oleo.
Be sure oleo melts.
Add sugar and Bran.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk, salt and baking soda. Sift and add flour and Kellogg's All-Bran.
Store batter in refrigerator until ready to use.
Do not stir batter when filling muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ione's carrot cake
directions: Mix up and cook 2 hours at 300°. Cook in a tube pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar together thoroughly.
Add mashed bananas and blend.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts last. Pour into well greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 1 regular or 2 small loaf pans.
Fill 3/4 full.
This recipe doubles well.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup tap water, the mayonnaise and vanilla.
Beat for about 2 minutes on low to medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with Cream Cheese filling or your choice.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
Combine with onion and green pepper in a bowl. Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: fudgy no baked cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown beef and add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.

title: blueberry pastries
directions: In small bowl, mix cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Separate crescent roll dough into four rectangles.
Press perforations together on each rectangle.
Brush rectangles with melted margarine.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture on 3 rectangles.
Top with blueberries.
Stack 3 blueberry rectangles on top of each other, then top with plain rectangle.
Cut rectangle stack crosswise in half.
Cut each half diagonally into 2 triangles.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Place on cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mini sausage appetizers
directions: Combine raw sausage and cheese in mixing bowl.
Add biscuit mix; blend thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes, or until brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 100.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook pepper, hamburger and seasoning.
Add tomatoes and corn meal.
Place in casserole and cover top of mixture with cheese. Bake about 20 minutes or until cheese melts, at 325°.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Mix cake mix and baking powder.
Drain fruit and use juice instead of water in cake mix.
Put fruit in bottom of well-greased cake pan or 6 1/2 x 10-inch baking pan.
Pour prepared mix over fruit. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until toothpick comes clean from the center.
One-half cup chopped nuts may be sprinkled over fruit or on top.
May be served in bowl with milk as cobbler.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and stir all together.
Pour in long greased pan.
Cook for 25 minutes or less at 350°.
Let cool.
After cake is cool, spread a 7-ounce jar of marshmallow cream on top.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and drain off most of the grease.
Saute onion.
Add catsup, mustard and brown sugar.
Mix well and combine with bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together the eggs, butter, sugar, vanilla and scalded milk.
Pour over bread and raisins.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top. Place casserole in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crispy rice candy
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat and add
cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares. Makes about 24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: snifwifs (aka mudhens)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and egg yolks.
Pack this crumbly mixture into a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat the egg whites until fluffy, then beat in the brown sugar.
Stir in nuts or chocolate chips.
Spread this topping on top of the first mixture; place the pan into a moderate oven for about 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bring to a boil, butter, cocoa, oil, and water.
Combine flour and sugar.
Add liquid mixture to flour and sugar.
Beat.
Add eggs, buttermilk, and vanilla and stir until ingredients are combined.
Mixture will be thin.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's 1600's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add other ingredients as listed.
Gradually add enough flour to make a stiff dough (about 2 1/2 pounds).
You may let the dough rest one hour before rolling (this is optional).
Roll and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown.
Eat and enjoy! Happy holidays.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts, soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Pour in large pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on foil to cool using a fork to separate.

title: icing for cake
directions: Cook together flour and milk until thick.
Cream cooked mixture with Spry.
Gradually add powdered sugar and vanilla.

title: aunt vera's chocolate icing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook until it forms a ball when placed in cup of cold water.

title: cream cheese spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Add cream cheese, onion and 1/2 sick of butter.
Put in small baking dish.
Put bread crumbs and melted butter on top.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cream salad
directions: Put marshmallows, sugar, jello and lemon juice in hot water. Put in refrigerator until it starts to jell. Add nuts, pineapple creamed with cheese, whipped cream and salt. Mix together. Pour all ingredients into mold or dish.
(Grease mold with salad dressing.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw out bread.
Butter an angel food pan.
Tear off pieces of bread and roll in butter (walnut size pieces).
Place in bottom of pan, continuing this until bread is completely used.
Follow cooking directions on bread package, only cook a little longer. When done, turn onto a plate and serve hot.

title: ana z.'s crazy cake
directions: Mix two eggs, margarine and cake mix.
Mixture will be very thick.
Spread into greased and floured pan.
Spread pineapple on top.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs. Pour over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn oven off and let cake stand in oven for 30 minutes longer.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix the soda and water.
Pour over raisins and let stand overnight without stirring.
Sift together the dry ingredients and stir into raisins with spoon.
Add oil and mix well.
Stir in nuts.

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine cake mix, eggs, water, flour and oil in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place sliced bananas on top. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Top with walnuts or pecans.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: sorta lasagne
directions: Mix egg into Ricotta cheese.
Mix all ingredients together in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may substitute cottage cheese for Ricotta.
I also add about 1 pound of ground beef, cooked and drained.

title: lillie mae whittaker's salad dressing
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter together. Beat in mustard and eggs.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, to a good rolling boil.
Pour hot over potatoes or coleslaw.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamed.
Add beaten eggs to sugar mixture and blend.
Add milk and sweet potatoes and blend. Add vanilla and coconut.

title: tabouli
directions: Pour boiling water over bulgur wheat; let set for 1/2 hour. In separate bowl, mix together oil, lemon juice, salt and garlic powder, then stir.
Add tomatoes and olives to wheat mixture; mix. Next pour in oil mixture and stir well.
Chill for a few hours, then serve.

title: mexican beans
directions: Cook beans with onion until almost done.
Add garlic salt, pepper, cumin, salt, pepper, green chili, yellow chili and green chilies and cook 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, ground beef and butter.
Cook 30 minutes longer.

title: jan's quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, warm water and sugar.
Let stand 16 minutes.
Cut
shortening
into flour, baking powder and salt. Combine the
two
mixtures
and knead dough adding flour until dough is not
sticky.
Make
rolls
and
let
rise 30 minutes. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad(coca-cola salad)
directions: Mix jello and water. Add cream cheese and mix real well.
Add pineapple, Coke, nuts and cherries. Mix well. Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: new mexico peanut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients.
Bake in pie shell at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot pepper pecans
directions: For each cup of large pecan halves, melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a shallow pan.
Spread pecans evenly in one layer and bake in a slow oven (300°) for 30 minutes.
Stir several times during the baking.
Mix 2 teaspoons of soy sauce, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 3 dashes liquid hot pepper.
Pour into toasted nuts, turning them so the seasonings will be evenly distributed.
Spread on double thickness of paper towels to cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix gelatin, pineapple, nuts and chill until firm.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop up everything.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Toss with cheese.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Pour on dressing.
Chill. Eat and enjoy.

title: kartoffelklosse(potato dumplings)
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain and mash or force through sieve or food mill.
Spread on paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Beat eggs to blend in a medium-sized bowl.
Add potatoes and other ingredients to eggs and mix until blended. Shape into balls about the size of large walnuts.
Add more bread crumbs if mixture is too soft to handle.
Drop balls into boiling salted water.
After they rise to the surface, cook about 3 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Serves six.

title: easy yeast balls
directions: Mix together yeast and water and set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients, then mix in yeast and water.
Make this mixture at least 24 hours before using.
Put in a sealed bowl in refrigerator. This will keep about 1 week, but best if used within the first 4 days.
When ready to use, grease muffin tins and spoon in mixture about 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° until done or test with toothpick.

title: hot sausage and cheese balls
directions: Brown sausage and crumble; drain fat and cool.
Combine all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Cool on wire rack or paper towels.

title: hawaiian pineapple dreamboat
directions: In blender, place cottage cheese, pineapple juice, sweetener and the extracts.
Process until smooth.
Place banana strips in bottom of medium size dessert dish.
Pour cottage cheese mixture over the bananas.
Top with crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate one hour before eating.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tapioca pudding salad
directions: Cook tapioca puddings in water for 3 minutes.
Add gelatin, then cool until slightly jelled.
Drain pineapple thoroughly; add, along with whipped cream to the pudding mixture.
This salad does not get stiff enough to set in a mold, so put in a dish and refrigerate.
Whipped topping may be substituted for whipped cream.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Prepare gelatin using 2 cups of water.
Let cool and set in soft gel (do not put in icebox).
This takes about 3 hours.
Whip vigorously.
Put cottage cheese through a food mill or press with the back of a spoon through a strainer.
Add to pineapple, mayonnaise, salt and lemon.
Chill in 12 individual molds or a 2-quart flat Pyrex dish which has been greased with mayonnaise. Serves 12.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Stew mincemeat and water until thick. Cream sugar and shortening (melted and cooled). Add egg and salt. Dissolve the soda and put in mincemeat mixture. Add baking powder and flour. Drop on buttered baking sheet by teaspoon. Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese and cauliflower chowder
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in water until tender.
Add cauliflower, undrained mushrooms, bouillon granules and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer the vegetable mixture about 8 minutes, or until cauliflower is just tender.
In screw-top jar, combine milk and cornstarch; shake well. Stir into hot vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in shredded cheese and pimento. Heat through, stirring to melt cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water.
Heat slowly until gelatin is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Add apple juice and chill until syrupy.
Fold in remaining ingredients and pour into a 1 quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: peggy mcconnell's favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine everything and pat into dish or loaf pan.
Score with a spoon handle and fill score marks with ketchup.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Mix together the beef, onion and egg.
Combine soup and water. Add 4 tablespoons soup to beef mixture (save rest of soup for later).
Add enough bread crumbs so meat will hold together.
Form into balls; brown in small amount of oil on both sides.
Pour off grease.
Put rest of soup on top of meatballs and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: old fashioned hickory nut cake
directions: This makes a three layer cake or cut one cake in half and place one half on top of the other and in this way have a cake and a half.

title: glazed pork roast
directions: Place roast in roast or baking pan.
Insert meat thermometer in thickest part of roast.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven about 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: fresh red chili sauce
directions: Remove chile stems, seeds and bad spots.
Rinse chiles in cold water.
Soak chiles in cold water 1 to 2 hours, until pods are tender.
Place chile in blender with 1 to 2 cups water.
Blend chile until it resembles tomato sauce in consistency.
Saute onion in butter.
Add chile and seasoning to onion.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Makes
1 quart.

title: german scalloped sauerkraut
directions: Layer in casserole the sauerkraut, apples and brown sugar. Cover and bake at 350° until apples are tender. Delicious served with pork.

title: polly baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain and save 6 tablespoons grease.
In a saucepan, warm ketchup, onion, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar, King syrup, baking molasses and bacon grease until hot.
Stir bacon into beans, then pour sauce over beans in a baking pan.
(Best to use an old iron pot.)
Stir every now and then after it bubbles. Don't let it get too thick;
best when juicy.
Bake at 350° until the way you like them (thick or thin).

title: fruit punch for fifty
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add the grated lemon and orange rind. Boil gently for 10 minutes.
Let mixture cool, then add the juice of 3 lemons.
Chill and when ready to serve, add chilled pineapple juice, orange juice and ginger ale.
Base can be made several days in advance and stored in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except tortillas and cheese. Dip tortillas in hot oil until soft.
Fill with chicken mixture. Roll and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into bell shapes, using cold pack containers lined with plastic wrap.
Chill until firm; unmold. Garnish with whipped parsley and pimiento strips.
Yield: 2 bells.

title: pudding cake dessert
directions: Mix and cook cake as directed; cool.
Mix vanilla pudding and milk together (2 cups milk per box pudding); let set overnight. Drain pineapple.
Mix sour cream, pineapple, Cool Whip and pie filling together with pudding.
Cut cake into small pieces; stir into pudding mixture.
Let set a while.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon plus 1 1/2 teaspoons Crisco oil and flour in medium skillet.
Stir constantly until rich, dark brown.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook a few minutes.
Set aside.
Heat remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in large saucepan on medium heat.
Add celery and onions.
Cook until soft and transparent.
Add okra.
Cook until okra ceases to rope, about 30 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, water, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Stir in shrimp mixture. Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes, adding tomato paste after 15 minutes. Add lobster meat.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serve in flat bottom bowls over rice.

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions (adjust amount according to number of people).
Drain.
Cut cheese into cubes and set aside.
Melt butter or margarine in bottom of pan.
Pour in cooked macaroni.
Add onion, salt, pepper and cheese cubes.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add to macaroni and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or to desired crispness.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute the onion in margarine.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: crazy cake
directions: In a large bowl, measure the first 3 ingredients and mix.
In a saucepan bring to a boil water, cocoa and margarine.
Add boiled mixture to sugar and flour.
Mix and add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and baking soda.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan (10 x 15-inch). Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple, reserving the liquid. Melt the butter in a deep 9-inch oven-proof skillet.
Stir in the brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of the reserved pineapple rings in the pan, filling all centers with cherry halves.
Set aside.
Beat shortening, sugar and egg together until well-blended, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Measure the remaining pineapple juice and add water if necessary to make 2/3 cup.
Add the dry mixture and pineapple juice with vanilla to the shortening mixture alternately and beat.
Pour over pineapple rings and place in oven.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done in middle.
Cool 5 minutes and invert cake onto plate.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hot and spicy mexican dip
directions: Spread refried bean mixture over large plate.
Using approximately 1/3 jar picante sauce mixed in with beans, taste until you get the hot and spicy flavor desired.
Spread over top jalapenos, tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Decorate with spoonfuls of sour cream and enjoy with choice of tortilla chips.

title: rob's favorite ham meat balls
directions: Mix together and make into large balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then pour off grease.
Add sauce to meat balls and put back in oven for an additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add yeast to warm (110°) water in medium size bowl.
Let stand a few minutes. Stir to dissolve.
Mix in half the flour, salt and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Mix or knead in remaining flour. Cover and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Divide into 2 parts. Dip fingers into oil and pat out each half of dough onto greased baking sheet, making 11-inch rounds.
Make edges thicker and brush with oil. Use favorite pizza sauce and toppings. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Sift sugar and flour.
Melt margarine; cut in flour and sugar to make crumbs.
Set aside 1/2 cup.
Beat in the rest of the ingredients, adding the soda in boiling water last.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: louisiana cheese ball
directions: With fork, mix cheese real well.
Add onion and Accent.
Mix well.
Take 5 slices of beef, chopped real fine and add to cheese; mix well.
Spread on platter of your choice, thick or thin.
Take remaining beef and lay it all over your cheese ball until covered. Let set in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Eat well with crackers.

title: nancy's apple cake
directions: Mix together salad oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix flour mixture slowly into egg mixture.
Mix all together well with wooden spoon.
Fold in peeled, diced apples.
Bake in 10 x 14-inch cake pan for 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Dust with powdered sugar or frost as desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost
hash
brown
potatoes
and
combine in a large mixing bowl with 1/2 cup butter.
Season with salt and pepper. Add onion, sour cream, chicken soup and grated cheese.
Blend ingredients
well.
Pour into 3-quart buttered casserole dish. When
ready
to
bake,
mix
crushed potato chips with 1/4 cup melted
butter and spread on top of casserole.
Cover and bake for 45
minutes
Remove cover and allow to brown for about 15 minutes.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli, raisins, pecans and onion in Ziploc until ready to eat.
Marinate mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar overnight. Toss all together and add bacon.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions or I steam broccoli.
Mix cooked broccoli with soup, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle casserole with cheese and then top with sliced almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until cheese is melted, approximately 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook cake until done.

title: old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and spices and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, applesauce, raisins, nuts and dates.
Add dry ingredients; mix well, then dissolve soda in 1/4 cup hot water and add last.
Bake in tube pan, slowly, about an hour or until done.
Especially good served with whipped cream.

title: christmas reindeer cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Slowly add flour until makes a ball.
For best results, chill half hour or more.
Roll out on floured surface.
Use any type cookie cutter (we prefer reindeer in our family).
Place on cookie sheets sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until edges are brown.
Cool on rack for frosting.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut up cooked
chicken,
as
much
as
you want.
Saute celery and onion.	Grate cheese.
Cook spaghetti.	Mix together and season
generously with garlic powder, salt and pepper. No further cooking
is
needed because hot spaghetti melts the cheese.

title: sweet hot new potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart glass casserole, combine potatoes and 1/2 cup water.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 to 11 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand 2 minutes.
In a 4-cup glass measure, combine onions and butter.
Cook on High 2 to 5 minutes until onion is translucent.
Stir in sugar, salt and flour.
Add half the milk.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add remaining milk; cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Cook at 50% power for 2 minutes.
Drain potatoes and stir in sauce.
Serves 6.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, celery, green pepper, onion, pimento and salt in large nonaluminum bowl.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain well.

title: plantation fruit bars
directions: Cream thoroughly shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg, molasses and dark syrup.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients to cream mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins or dates.
Spread in greased shallow 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.
Spread cool bars with powdered sugar frosting.

title: my mother's cheese crunchies
directions: Mix cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with beater.
Press half of cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 5 to 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in milk.
Spread over cake.
Then sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Top with remaining half of cake batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine forst 2 ingredients.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 c. for topping. 2. Add brown sugar and cinnamon to reserved topping mix.
Mix well.
Set aside. 3. Press remaining mixture on ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Arrange sliced apples over base.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Spread evenly over apples. 4. Sprinkle reserved topping mix over all.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: microwave potatoes and onions
directions: Using a 2 qt. casserole dish, layer potatoes and onions. Slice margarine over top and sprinkle with salt. Cook about 15 minutes in microwave. Turn or stir lightly and cook 15 minutes more or until done. Time may vary.

title: fig cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk and add flour to batter.
Add figs and nuts.
Add cinnamon and cloves;
add salt.	Cook at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine and bring to a simmer.
Simmer several minutes.
Serve piping hot in cups.
Give each person 1 cinnamon stick to stir with, also adds that extra special taste to the drink.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs, baking powder, sugar, oil, vanilla and squash.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans for about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: potato beef casserole
directions: Put half of potatoes on bottom of a greased casserole.
Add 1/2 of ground beef, then onion.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup and milk; pour over ingredients.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Cook hamburger with onion (drain grease).
Add pizza sauce, mushrooms, green pepper and simmer until well done.
Put on English muffin half; top with slice of American cheese.
Place in toaster oven or regular oven and melt cheese.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix together well. Can be used on steaks, pork chops or chicken.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Blend the first five ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Cool completely. Put aside half of crumb mixture.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat sugar, oleo and egg until smooth. Add bananas, peels and milk; mix well.
Add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan; bake 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: old fashioned toll house cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; beat in eggs and blend in flour. Stir in chocolate chips by hand.
Drop large tablespoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for eight minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar, add eggs one at a time, rotating with dry ingredients and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use tube pan.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and make small balls about the size of a nickel.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: herbed potatoes in olive oil
directions: Combine oil, herbs, garlic, salt and pepper in large bowl. Soak potatoes in cold water 5 minutes.
Change water once.
Drain potatoes.
Pat dry.
Add to bowl.
Turn to coat well.
Spread into 12 x 14-inch baking dish.
Bake until edges are brown, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.

title: swedish slaw recipe
directions: Grate cabbage and onion together.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Boil 1/3 cup sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt, celery seed and oil together. Pour this mixture over cabbage while hot.
Let set at least 4 hours before serving.
Keeps for several days.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar, cornstarch and Karo.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add red food coloring and Jell-O to hot mixture.
Put aside and let cool.
When cool, pour 1/2 of Jell-O mixture into pie shell.
Add whole strawberries, then put remaining Jell-O mixture.
Top with whipped cream.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: eggplant antipasto
directions: Put eggplant, pepper, onion, mushrooms and oil in skillet. Cover and cook gently 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Simmer, covered, until eggplant is tender, about 30 minutes. Serve warm or cold. Yield: 1 quart.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add apples and nuts.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Bake in oblong pan at 325° for 1 hour.
This is just the right amount for a foil lasagna pan. Freezes well.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Beat egg whites and dash of salt until it forms a peak. Gradually add 1 cup sugar while beating until mixed. Add nuts and stir until thoroughly coated with sugar mixture. Preheat oven to 350° and melt butter in roasting pan. Spread coated nuts over melted butter and bake 30 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon every 10 minutes or so.

title: lasagna al forno
directions: Saute chopped onions in olive oil.
Add ground beef and season to taste with salt, pepper, oregano and garlic.
Finally add peeled tomatoes (including juice), and sour cream.

title: seafood au gratin
directions: Cut seafood into bite size pieces; arrange them in a baking dish.
Mix butter and flour over low heat; stir in milk and grated cheese.
When slightly thickened, add wine.
Pour sauce over seafood; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, until browned.
Serve over plain white rice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread Crescent Rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake until brown. Mix cream cheese, ranch dressing and mayonnaise in bowl and set aside.
When crust is cool, sprinkle/spread on vegetables and sprinkle on cheese.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: fruit tapioca
directions: Drain fruit juice into a measuring cup.
Cut fruit into bite size pieces and set aside.
Add water to fruit juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Put all ingredients except fruit into a saucepan. Let set 5 minutes, then bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat; add fruit and stir occasionally while cooling.
Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry sponge cake(easy diet dessert)
directions: Slice sponge cake (homemade or store bought) in half.
Layer with fresh berries and 1/2 of the lite Cool Whip.
Place remaining berries on top and add remaining Cool Whip over berries.
Pour any juice you might have left over the top.
Let cool in refrigerator about 20 minutes.
You may use other fruits in place of strawberries.

title: hush puppies southern style
directions: Mix all ingredients, only adding enough milk to make a thick dough.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: pat's cheese ball
directions: Make sure bell pepper and onion are finely chopped.
Mix first 4 ingredients and shape in a ball.
Chop up the beef into small pieces and roll ball in it.
Let chill for a couple of hours. Serve with crackers.

title: mushroom and brown rice skillet
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add rest of ingredients to saucepan or skillet.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Cover and cook 50 minutes without stirring until water is absorbed.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Mix coloring with cocoa and add to shortening and sugar mixture.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add buttermilk and flour in 3 steps, beginning with buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar and add to batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with following frosting.

title: victoria sandwich
directions: Bake cake in layers as directed.
Split one layer in half to make 2 layers.
Fill with 1/2 cup jelly or preserves.
Top with remaining half layer and sift confectioners sugar over top.
Serve in wedges.
Use other layer for another dessert.

title: marinade
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours, turning at least twice.

title: hoagie
directions: Brown
ground
beef
until well done; drain excess fat. Peel potatoes
and slice into 1/4-inch thick slices; do onion the
same way.
After meat has cooked, pour into baking dish, layer potatoes on top, then onion rings;
pour English peas on top of this.
Take the package of onion gravy and mix with 3/4 cup
of hot water;
pour over entire casserole.
Cover; place in
350° oven for 30 minutes.
Can be cooked on top of stove. Place in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Turn down and let slow simmer until potatoes are done, do not stir.

title: marcella's brown sugar rounds
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and egg.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well. Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased sheet 2-inches apart.
(Dough will flatten and spread during baking.) Bake 10 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion in a large bowl.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables and toss well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Drain off vinegar and stir in:

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in 2 gallons of water and cover sliced tomatoes. Soak 24 hours; rinse thoroughly and place in clear water.
Let set in clear water one hour; then change at 1 hour intervals (4 times in clear water in all).
Drain well.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices; bring to a boil.
Pour over drained, sliced tomatoes and simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.

title: honey and herb grilled pork
directions: Mix all ingredients and add pork.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes per pound, basting occasionally.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch microwaveproof loaf pan.
Cook on 70 for 18 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine condensed milk and water in mixer bowl; mix well. Beat in pudding mix.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Dip banana slices into lemon juice.
Layer pudding, vanilla wafers and banana slices in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Chill thoroughly.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Fry onions
in	oil
until golden brown.
Add mushrooms and cook for
5 minutes.
Remove mixture to small bowl.
Brown meat in a
skillet.
(We use cooked roast beef.) Peel and chop tomatoes. Sprinkle
flour
over
browned
meat and stir well. Add
tomatoes and
their
juice.
Add
salt,	pepper	and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover skillet, turn to low heat and let mixture
cook
for 1	hour, stirring occasionally.
(If using previously
cooked beef, lower this cooking time to 1/2 hour.) Add onion and mushroom mixture and sour cream to meat mixture. Stir well
and
cook
on low temperature, covered, for 30 minutes.
This is great served with noodles or baked potatoes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg, then pumpkin.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: french tomato soup dressing
directions: Combine well the oil, vinegar, soup and Worcestershire sauce. Add the sugar, salt, dry mustard, paprika, cloves, garlic and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into clean sterile jars and refrigerate.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in bite size pieces and cook in small amount of water for five minutes.
Drain squash.
Mix soup, onion, pimento, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold in squash.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and celery 10 to 12 minutes.
Add other ingredients.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix well and let stand 15 minutes in covered bowl before using.
You can thin this a little and use for onion rings or mushrooms.
Store in a covered container.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter.
Add crumbs, vanilla, sugar and mix.
Stir in peanut butter.
Shape into small balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until hard.
Melt chocolate.
Dip each ball in chocolate.
Place on foil or waxed paper.
Refrigerate again or freeze.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix with melted margarine for pie crust.
Pat into an 11 x 14-inch pan, reserving a small amount. Dissolve gelatin in one cup hot water.
Set aside to cool.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles as directed on package.
Brown beef with onion in skillet. Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, garlic salt, basil, oregano, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and water.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Combine cottage cheese, egg and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.

In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, meat mixture and Mozzarella cheese, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix shrimp with cream cheese.
Make into a ball.
Mix the cocktail sauce with about 1/2 bottle of horseradish and pour over ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: pink lady dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator for about 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: You will also need 1 plastic bag.

title: chicken salad amandine with frozen fruit salad(from rich's magnolia room)
directions: Makes 12 servings.
Preparation Time: 15 minutes.
Freezing Time: 3 hours.
Standing Time: 15 minutes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cream cheese and blend on low speed with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients; chill.
May be used as a molded salad or served on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Lightly butter a shallow 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle rice over bottom of dish.
In a large bowl, combine undiluted soups and margarine.
Lay chicken pieces on rice. Spread soup mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove cover and turn oven to 400°. Brown chicken about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Chop onion.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar together; pour over broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling water (salted) 5 minutes; drain.
Cook beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Add 1 cup of tomato sauce
Heat through.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place peppers upright in ungreased baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Make white cake like the box indicates, except when it calls for 1 1/4 cups water, add 1 cup water and 1/4 cup creme de menthe instead.
When cake is done, poke holes in the cake going at least 1/2 way down with the handle of a wooden spoon.
